7377 WasmBytecodeGenerator::WasmBytecodeGenerator(uint32_t function_index,
7378  InterpreterCode* wasm_code,
7379  const WasmModule* module)
7380  : const_slot_offset_(0),
7381  slot_offset_(0),
7382  ref_slots_count_(0),
7383  function_index_(function_index),
7384  wasm_code_(wasm_code),
7385  args_count_(0),
7386  args_slots_size_(0),
7387  return_count_(0),
7388  rets_slots_size_(0),
7389  locals_count_(0),
7390  current_block_index_(-1),
7391  is_instruction_reachable_(true),
7392  unreachable_block_count_(0),
7393 #ifdef DEBUG
7394  was_current_instruction_reachable_(true),
7395 #endif // DEBUG
7396  module_(module),
7397  last_instr_offset_(kInvalidCodeOffset),
7398  handler_size_(InstrHandlerSize::Large),
7399  current_instr_encoding_failed_(false)
7400 #ifdef DEBUG
7401  ,
7402  no_nested_emit_instr_handler_guard_(false)
7403 #endif // DEBUG
7404 {
7405  DCHECK(v8_flags.wasm_jitless);
7406 
7407  // Multiple memories not supported.
7408  DCHECK_LE(module->memories.size(), 1);
7409 
7410  size_t wasm_code_size = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
7411  code_.reserve(wasm_code_size * 6);
7412  slots_.reserve(wasm_code_size / 2);
7413  stack_.reserve(wasm_code_size / 4);
7414  blocks_.reserve(wasm_code_size / 8);
7415 
7416  const FunctionSig* sig = module_->functions[function_index].sig;
7417  args_count_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->parameter_count());
7418  args_slots_size_ = WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig);
7419  return_count_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->return_count());
7420  rets_slots_size_ = WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig);
7421  locals_count_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(wasm_code->locals.num_locals);
7422 
7423  is_memory64_ = IsMemory64();
7424  if (is_memory64_) {
7425  int_mem_push_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I64Push;
7426  int_mem_pop_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I64Pop;
7427  } else {
7428  int_mem_push_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I32Push;
7429  int_mem_pop_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I32Pop;
7430  }
7431 }
7432 
7433 size_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::Simd128Hash::operator()(
7434  const Simd128& s128) const {
7435  static_assert(sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(uint64_t));
7436  const int64x2 s = s128.to_i64x2();
7437  return s.val[0] ^ s.val[1];
7438 }
7439 
7440 // Look if the slot that hold the value at {stack_index} is being shared with
7441 // other slots. This can happen if there are multiple load.get operations that
7442 // copy from the same local.
7443 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::HasSharedSlot(uint32_t stack_index) const {
7444  // Only consider stack entries added in the current block.
7445  // We don't need to consider ancestor blocks because if a block has a
7446  // non-empty signature we always pass arguments and results into separate
7447  // slots, emitting CopySlot operations.
7448  uint32_t start_slot_index = blocks_[current_block_index_].stack_size_;
7449 
7450  for (uint32_t i = start_slot_index; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
7451  if (stack_[i] == stack_[stack_index]) {
7452  return true;
7453  }
7454  }
7455  return false;
7456 }
7457 
7458 // Look if the slot that hold the value at {stack_index} is being shared with
7459 // other slots. This can happen if there are multiple load.get operations that
7460 // copy from the same local. In this case when we modify the value of the slot
7461 // with a local.set or local.tee we need to first duplicate the slot to make
7462 // sure that the old value is preserved in the other shared slots.
7463 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::FindSharedSlot(uint32_t stack_index,
7464  uint32_t* new_slot_index) {
7465  *new_slot_index = UINT_MAX;
7466  ValueType value_type = slots_[stack_[stack_index]].value_type;
7467  if (value_type.is_reference()) return false;
7468 
7469  // Only consider stack entries added in the current block.
7470  // We don't need to consider ancestor blocks because if a block has a
7471  // non-empty signature we always pass arguments and results into separate
7472  // slots, emitting CopySlot operations.
7473  uint32_t start_slot_index = blocks_[current_block_index_].stack_size_;
7474 
7475  for (uint32_t i = start_slot_index; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
7476  if (stack_[i] == stack_[stack_index]) {
7477  // Allocate new slot to preserve the old value of a shared slot.
7478  *new_slot_index = CreateSlot(value_type);
7479  break;
7480  }
7481  }
7482 
7483  if (*new_slot_index == UINT_MAX) return false;
7484 
7485  // If there was a collision and we allocated a new slot to preserve the old
7486  // value, we need to do two things to keep the state up to date:
7487  // 1. For each shared slot, we update the stack value to refer to the new
7488  // slot. This track the change at bytecode generation time.
7489  // 2. We return {true} to indicate that the slot was shared and the caller
7490  // should emit a 's2s_PreserveCopySlot...' instruction to copy the old slot
7491  // value into the new slot, at runtime.
7492 
7493  // This loop works because stack_index is always greater or equal to the index
7494  // of args/globals.
7495  DCHECK_GT(start_slot_index, stack_index);
7496  for (uint32_t i = start_slot_index; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
7497  if (stack_[i] == stack_[stack_index]) {
7498  // Copy value into the new slot.
7499  UpdateStack(i, *new_slot_index);
7500 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7501  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
7502  v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
7503  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7504  EmitStackIndex(i);
7505  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[*new_slot_index].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
7506  printf("Preserve UpdateStack: [%d] = %d\n", i,
7507  slots_[*new_slot_index].slot_offset);
7508  }
7509  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7510  }
7511 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7512  }
7513  }
7514 
7515  return true;
7516 }
7517 
7518 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::EmitCopySlot(ValueType value_type,
7519  uint32_t from_slot_index,
7520  uint32_t to_slot_index,
7521  bool copy_from_reg) {
7522  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
7523  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
7524  switch (kind) {
7525  case kI32:
7526  if (copy_from_reg) {
7527  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyR0ToSlot32);
7528  } else {
7529  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot32);
7530  }
7531  break;
7532  case kI64:
7533  if (copy_from_reg) {
7534  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyR0ToSlot64);
7535  } else {
7536  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot64);
7537  }
7538  break;
7539  case kF32:
7540  if (copy_from_reg) {
7541  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyFp0ToSlot32);
7542  } else {
7543  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot32);
7544  }
7545  break;
7546  case kF64:
7547  if (copy_from_reg) {
7548  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyFp0ToSlot64);
7549  } else {
7550  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot64);
7551  }
7552  break;
7553  case kS128:
7554  DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7555  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot128);
7556  break;
7557  case kRef:
7558  case kRefNull:
7559  DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7560  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlotRef);
7561  break;
7562  default:
7563  UNREACHABLE();
7564  }
7565 
7566  if (kind == kRefNull || kind == kRef) {
7567  DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7568  EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[from_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7569  EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[to_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7570  } else {
7571  if (!copy_from_reg) {
7572  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset);
7573  }
7574  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset);
7575  }
7576  }
7577  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7578 
7579 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7580  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_bytecode_generator &&
7581  v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
7582  printf("emit CopySlot: %d(%d) -> %d(%d)\n", from_slot_index,
7583  slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset, to_slot_index,
7584  slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset);
7585  }
7586 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7587 }
7588 
7589 // When a Wasm function starts the values for the function args and locals are
7590 // already present in the Wasm stack. The stack entries for args and locals
7591 // can be directly accessed with {local.get} and modified with {local.set} and
7592 // {local.tee}, but they can never be popped, they are always present until
7593 // the function returns.
7594 // During the execution of the function other values are then pushed/popped
7595 // into/from the stack, but these other entries are only accessible indirectly
7596 // as operands/results of operations, not directly with local.get/set
7597 // instructions.
7598 //
7599 // DrumBrake implements a "args/locals propagation" optimization that allows the
7600 // stack slots for "local" stack entries to be shared with other stack entries
7601 // (using the {stack_} and {slots_} arrays), in order to avoid emitting calls to
7602 // 'local.get' instruction handlers.
7603 
7604 // When an arg/local value is modified, and its slot is shared with other
7605 // entries in the stack, we need to preserve the old value of the stack entry in
7606 // a new slot.
7607 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::CopyToSlot(ValueType value_type,
7608  uint32_t from_slot_index,
7609  uint32_t to_stack_index,
7610  bool copy_from_reg) {
7611  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
7612  uint32_t to_slot_index = stack_[to_stack_index];
7613  DCHECK(copy_from_reg || CheckEqualKind(kind, slots_[from_slot_index].kind()));
7614  DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(slots_[to_slot_index].kind(), kind));
7615 
7616  uint32_t new_slot_index;
7617  // If the slot is shared {FindSharedSlot} creates a new slot and makes all the
7618  // 'non-locals' stack entries that shared the old slot point to this new slot.
7619  // We need to emit a {PreserveCopySlot} instruction to dynamically copy the
7620  // old value into the new slot.
7621  if (FindSharedSlot(to_stack_index, &new_slot_index)) {
7622  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
7623  switch (kind) {
7624  case kI32:
7625  if (copy_from_reg) {
7626  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyR0ToSlot32);
7627  } else {
7628  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot32);
7629  }
7630  break;
7631  case kI64:
7632  if (copy_from_reg) {
7633  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyR0ToSlot64);
7634  } else {
7635  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot64);
7636  }
7637  break;
7638  case kF32:
7639  if (copy_from_reg) {
7640  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyFp0ToSlot32);
7641  } else {
7642  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot32);
7643  }
7644  break;
7645  case kF64:
7646  if (copy_from_reg) {
7647  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyFp0ToSlot64);
7648  } else {
7649  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot64);
7650  }
7651  break;
7652  case kS128:
7653  DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7654  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot128);
7655  break;
7656  case kRef:
7657  case kRefNull:
7658  default:
7659  UNREACHABLE();
7660  }
7661 
7662  if (kind == kRefNull || kind == kRef) {
7663  DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7664  EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[from_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7665  EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[to_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7666  EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[new_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7667  } else {
7668  if (!copy_from_reg) {
7669  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset);
7670  }
7671  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset);
7672  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[new_slot_index].slot_offset);
7673  }
7674 
7675 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7676  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
7677  v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
7678  printf("emit s2s_PreserveCopySlot: %d %d %d\n",
7679  slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset,
7680  slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset,
7681  slots_[new_slot_index].slot_offset);
7682  }
7683 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7684  }
7685  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7686  } else {
7687  EmitCopySlot(value_type, from_slot_index, to_slot_index, copy_from_reg);
7688  }
7689 }
7690 
7691 // Used for 'local.tee' and 'local.set' instructions.
7692 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::CopyToSlotAndPop(ValueType value_type,
7693  uint32_t to_stack_index,
7694  bool is_tee, bool copy_from_reg) {
7695  DCHECK(!stack_.empty());
7696  DCHECK_LT(to_stack_index, stack_.size() - (copy_from_reg ? 0 : 1));
7697 
7698  // LocalGet uses a "copy-on-write" mechanism: the arg/local value is not
7699  // copied and instead the stack entry references the same slot. When the
7700  // arg/local value is modified, we need to preserve the old value of the stack
7701  // entry in a new slot.
7702  CopyToSlot(value_type, stack_.back(), to_stack_index, copy_from_reg);
7703 
7704  if (!is_tee && !copy_from_reg) {
7705  PopSlot();
7706 
7707 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7708  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7709  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_PopSlot) {}
7710  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7711  }
7712 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7713  }
7714 }
7715 
7716 // This function is called when we enter a new 'block', 'loop' or 'if' block
7717 // statement. Checks whether any of the 'non-locals' stack entries share a slot
7718 // with an arg/local stack entry. In that case stop make sure the local stack
7719 // entry will get its own slot. This is necessary because at runtime we could
7720 // jump at the block after having modified the local value in some other code
7721 // path.
7722 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) - Understand why this is not required only for
7723 // 'loop' blocks.
7724 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PreserveArgsAndLocals() {
7725  uint32_t num_args_and_locals = args_count_ + locals_count_;
7726 
7727  // If there are only args/locals entries in the stack, nothing to do.
7728  if (num_args_and_locals >= stack_size()) return;
7729 
7730  for (uint32_t local_index = 0; local_index < num_args_and_locals;
7731  ++local_index) {
7732  uint32_t new_slot_index;
7733  if (FindSharedSlot(local_index, &new_slot_index)) {
7734  ValueType value_type = slots_[stack_[local_index]].value_type;
7735  EmitCopySlot(value_type, stack_[local_index], new_slot_index);
7736  }
7737  }
7738 }
7739 
7740 uint32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::ReserveBlockSlots(
7741  uint8_t opcode, const WasmInstruction::Optional::Block& block_data,
7742  size_t* rets_slots_count, size_t* params_slots_count) {
7743  uint32_t first_slot_index = 0;
7744  *rets_slots_count = 0;
7745  *params_slots_count = 0;
7746  bool first_slot_found = false;
7747  const ValueType value_type = block_data.value_type();
7748  if (value_type == kWasmBottom) {
7749  const FunctionSig* sig = module_->signature(block_data.sig_index);
7750  *rets_slots_count = sig->return_count();
7751  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < *rets_slots_count; i++) {
7752  uint32_t slot_index = CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(i));
7753  if (!first_slot_found) {
7754  first_slot_index = slot_index;
7755  first_slot_found = true;
7756  }
7757  }
7758  *params_slots_count = sig->parameter_count();
7759  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < *params_slots_count; i++) {
7760  uint32_t slot_index = CreateSlot(sig->GetParam(i));
7761  if (!first_slot_found) {
7762  first_slot_index = slot_index;
7763  first_slot_found = true;
7764  }
7765  }
7766  } else if (value_type != kWasmVoid) {
7767  *rets_slots_count = 1;
7768  first_slot_index = CreateSlot(value_type);
7769  }
7770  return first_slot_index;
7771 }
7772 
7773 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::StoreBlockParamsIntoSlots(
7774  uint32_t target_block_index, bool update_stack) {
7775  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
7776  blocks_[target_block_index];
7777  DCHECK_EQ(target_block_data.opcode_, kExprLoop);
7778 
7779  uint32_t params_count = ParamsCount(target_block_data);
7780  uint32_t rets_count = ReturnsCount(target_block_data);
7781  uint32_t first_param_slot_index =
7782  target_block_data.first_block_index_ + rets_count;
7783  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < params_count; i++) {
7784  uint32_t from_slot_index =
7785  stack_[stack_top_index() - (params_count - 1) + i];
7786  uint32_t to_slot_index = first_param_slot_index + i;
7787  if (from_slot_index != to_slot_index) {
7788  EmitCopySlot(GetParamType(target_block_data, i), from_slot_index,
7789  to_slot_index);
7790  if (update_stack) {
7791  DCHECK_EQ(GetParamType(target_block_data, i),
7792  slots_[first_param_slot_index + i].value_type);
7793  DCHECK_EQ(GetParamType(target_block_data, i),
7794  slots_[first_param_slot_index + i].value_type);
7795  UpdateStack(stack_top_index() - (params_count - 1) + i,
7796  first_param_slot_index + i);
7797 
7798 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7799  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7800  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7801  EmitStackIndex(stack_top_index() - (params_count - 1) + i);
7802  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[first_param_slot_index + i].slot_offset *
7803  kSlotSize);
7804  }
7805  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7806  }
7807 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7808  }
7809  }
7810  }
7811 }
7812 
7813 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(
7814  uint32_t target_block_index, WasmOpcode opcode) {
7815  bool is_branch = kExprBr == opcode || kExprBrIf == opcode ||
7816  kExprBrTable == opcode || kExprBrOnNull == opcode ||
7817  kExprBrOnNonNull == opcode || kExprBrOnCast == opcode;
7818  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
7819  blocks_[target_block_index];
7820  bool is_target_loop_block = target_block_data.opcode_ == kExprLoop;
7821  if (is_target_loop_block && is_branch) {
7822  StoreBlockParamsIntoSlots(target_block_index, false);
7823  }
7824 
7825  // Ignore params if this is the function main block.
7826  uint32_t params_count =
7827  target_block_index == 0 ? 0 : ParamsCount(target_block_data);
7828  uint32_t rets_count = ReturnsCount(target_block_data);
7829 
7830  // If we are branching to a loop block we go back to the beginning of the
7831  // block, therefore we don't need to store the block results.
7832  if (!is_target_loop_block || !is_branch) {
7833  // There could be valid code where there are not enough elements in the
7834  // stack if some code in unreachable (for example if a 'i32.const 0' is
7835  // followed by a 'br_if' the if branch is never reachable).
7836  uint32_t count = std::min(static_cast<uint32_t>(stack_.size()), rets_count);
7837  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < count; i++) {
7838  uint32_t from_slot_index = stack_[stack_top_index() - (count - 1) + i];
7839  uint32_t to_slot_index = target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i;
7840  if (from_slot_index != to_slot_index) {
7841  EmitCopySlot(GetReturnType(target_block_data, i), from_slot_index,
7842  to_slot_index);
7843  }
7844  }
7845  }
7846 
7847  bool is_else = (kExprElse == opcode);
7848  bool is_return = (kExprReturn == opcode);
7849  bool is_catch = (kExprCatch == opcode || kExprCatchAll == opcode);
7850  if (!is_branch && !is_return && !is_else && !is_catch) {
7851  uint32_t new_stack_height =
7852  target_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + rets_count;
7853  DCHECK(new_stack_height <= stack_.size() ||
7854  !was_current_instruction_reachable_);
7855  stack_.resize(new_stack_height);
7856 
7857  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < rets_count; i++) {
7858  DCHECK_EQ(GetReturnType(target_block_data, i),
7859  slots_[target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i].value_type);
7860  DCHECK_EQ(GetReturnType(target_block_data, i),
7861  slots_[target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i].value_type);
7862  UpdateStack(target_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i,
7863  target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i);
7864 
7865 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7866  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7867  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7868  EmitStackIndex(target_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i);
7869  EmitSlotOffset(
7870  slots_[target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i].slot_offset *
7871  kSlotSize);
7872  }
7873  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7874  }
7875 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7876  }
7877  }
7878 }
7879 
7880 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::RestoreIfElseParams(uint32_t if_block_index) {
7881  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& if_block_data =
7882  blocks_[if_block_index];
7883  DCHECK_EQ(if_block_data.opcode_, kExprIf);
7884 
7885  stack_.resize(blocks_[if_block_index].stack_size_);
7886  uint32_t params_count = if_block_index == 0 ? 0 : ParamsCount(if_block_data);
7887  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < params_count; i++) {
7888  UpdateStack(if_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i,
7889  if_block_data.GetParam(i), GetParamType(if_block_data, i));
7890 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7891  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7892  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7893  EmitStackIndex(if_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i);
7894  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[if_block_data.GetParam(i)].slot_offset *
7895  kSlotSize);
7896  }
7897  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7898  }
7899 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7900  }
7901 }
7902 
7903 uint32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::ScanConstInstructions() const {
7904  Decoder decoder(wasm_code_->start, wasm_code_->end);
7905  uint32_t const_slots_size = 0;
7906  pc_t pc = wasm_code_->locals.encoded_size;
7907  pc_t limit = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
7908  while (pc < limit) {
7909  uint32_t opcode = wasm_code_->start[pc];
7910  if (opcode == kExprI32Const || opcode == kExprF32Const) {
7911  const_slots_size += sizeof(uint32_t) / kSlotSize;
7912  } else if (opcode == kExprI64Const || opcode == kExprF64Const) {
7913  const_slots_size += sizeof(uint64_t) / kSlotSize;
7914  } else if (opcode == kSimdPrefix) {
7915  auto [opcode_index, opcode_len] =
7916  decoder.read_u32v<Decoder::FullValidationTag>(
7917  wasm_code_->start + pc + 1, "prefixed opcode index");
7918  opcode = (kSimdPrefix << 8) | opcode_index;
7919  if (opcode == kExprS128Const || opcode == kExprI8x16Shuffle) {
7920  const_slots_size += sizeof(Simd128) / kSlotSize;
7921  }
7922  }
7923  pc++;
7924  }
7925  return const_slots_size;
7926 }
7927 
7928 int32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::EndBlock(WasmOpcode opcode) {
7929  WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& block_data = blocks_[current_block_index_];
7930  bool is_try_catch =
7931  block_data.IsTry() || block_data.IsCatch() || block_data.IsCatchAll();
7932 
7933  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(current_block_index_, opcode);
7934 
7935  block_data.end_code_offset_ = CurrentCodePos();
7936  if (opcode == kExprEnd && block_data.IsElse()) {
7937  DCHECK_GT(block_data.if_else_block_index_, 0);
7938  blocks_[block_data.if_else_block_index_].end_code_offset_ =
7939  CurrentCodePos();
7940  }
7941 
7942  if (!is_try_catch) {
7943  current_block_index_ = blocks_[current_block_index_].parent_block_index_;
7944  }
7945 
7946  if (is_try_catch && (opcode == kExprEnd || opcode == kExprDelegate)) {
7947  int32_t try_block_index =
7948  eh_data_.EndTryCatchBlocks(current_block_index_, CurrentCodePos());
7949  DCHECK_GE(try_block_index, 0);
7950  current_block_index_ = blocks_[try_block_index].parent_block_index_;
7951  }
7952 
7953  last_instr_offset_ = kInvalidCodeOffset;
7954 
7955  return current_block_index_;
7956 }
7957 
7958 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::Return() {
7959  if (current_block_index_ >= 0) {
7960  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(0, kExprReturn);
7961  }
7962 
7963  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(s2s_Return) {
7964  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data = blocks_[0];
7965  uint32_t final_stack_size =
7966  target_block_data.stack_size_ + ReturnsCount(target_block_data);
7967  EmitStackIndex(final_stack_size);
7968  }
7969  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7970 }
7971 
7972 WasmInstruction WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeInstruction(pc_t pc,
7973  Decoder& decoder) {
7974  pc_t limit = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
7975  if (pc >= limit) return WasmInstruction();
7976 
7977  int len = 1;
7978  uint8_t orig = wasm_code_->start[pc];
7979  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(orig);
7980  if (WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) {
7981  uint32_t prefixed_opcode_length;
7982  std::tie(opcode, prefixed_opcode_length) =
7983  decoder.read_prefixed_opcode<Decoder::NoValidationTag>(
7984  wasm_code_->at(pc));
7985  // skip breakpoint by switching on original code.
7986  len = prefixed_opcode_length;
7987  }
7988 
7989  WasmInstruction::Optional optional;
7990  WasmDetectedFeatures detected;
7991  switch (orig) {
7992  case kExprUnreachable:
7993  break;
7994  case kExprNop:
7995  break;
7996  case kExprBlock:
7997  case kExprLoop:
7998  case kExprIf:
7999  case kExprTry: {
8000  BlockTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &detected, &decoder,
8001  wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8002  if (imm.sig_index.valid()) {
8003  // The block has at least one argument or at least two results, its
8004  // signature is identified by sig_index.
8005  optional.block.sig_index = imm.sig_index;
8006  optional.block.value_type_bitfield = kWasmBottom.raw_bit_field();
8007  } else if (imm.sig.return_count() + imm.sig.parameter_count() == 0) {
8008  // Void signature: no arguments and no results.
8009  optional.block.sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex::Invalid();
8010  optional.block.value_type_bitfield = kWasmVoid.raw_bit_field();
8011  } else {
8012  // No arguments and one result.
8013  optional.block.sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex::Invalid();
8014  std::optional<wasm::ValueType> wasm_return_type =
8015  GetWasmReturnTypeFromSignature(&imm.sig);
8016  DCHECK(wasm_return_type.has_value());
8017  optional.block.value_type_bitfield =
8018  wasm_return_type.value().raw_bit_field();
8019  }
8020  len = 1 + imm.length;
8021  break;
8022  }
8023  case kExprElse:
8024  break;
8025  case kExprCatch: {
8026  TagIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8027  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8028  optional.index = imm.index;
8029  len = 1 + imm.length;
8030  break;
8031  }
8032  case kExprCatchAll:
8033  break;
8034  case kExprEnd:
8035  break;
8036  case kExprThrow: {
8037  TagIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8038  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8039  len = 1 + imm.length;
8040  optional.index = imm.index;
8041  break;
8042  }
8043  case kExprRethrow:
8044  case kExprBr:
8045  case kExprBrIf:
8046  case kExprBrOnNull:
8047  case kExprBrOnNonNull:
8048  case kExprDelegate: {
8049  BranchDepthImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8050  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8051  len = 1 + imm.length;
8052  optional.depth = imm.depth;
8053  break;
8054  }
8055  case kExprBrTable: {
8056  BranchTableImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8057  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8058  BranchTableIterator<Decoder::NoValidationTag> iterator(&decoder, imm);
8059  optional.br_table.table_count = imm.table_count;
8060  optional.br_table.labels_index =
8061  static_cast<uint32_t>(br_table_labels_.size());
8062  for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= imm.table_count; i++) {
8063  DCHECK(iterator.has_next());
8064  br_table_labels_.emplace_back(iterator.next());
8065  }
8066  len = static_cast<int>(1 + iterator.pc() - imm.start);
8067  break;
8068  }
8069  case kExprReturn:
8070  break;
8071  case kExprCallFunction:
8072  case kExprReturnCall: {
8073  CallFunctionImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8074  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8075  len = 1 + imm.length;
8076  optional.index = imm.index;
8077  break;
8078  }
8079  case kExprCallIndirect:
8080  case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
8081  CallIndirectImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8082  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8083  len = 1 + imm.length;
8084  optional.indirect_call.table_index = imm.table_imm.index;
8085  optional.indirect_call.sig_index = imm.sig_imm.index.index;
8086  break;
8087  }
8088  case kExprDrop:
8089  break;
8090  case kExprSelect:
8091  break;
8092  case kExprSelectWithType: {
8093  SelectTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &detected, &decoder,
8094  wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8095  len = 1 + imm.length;
8096  break;
8097  }
8098  case kExprLocalGet: {
8099  IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "local index",
8100  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8101  len = 1 + imm.length;
8102  optional.index = imm.index;
8103  break;
8104  }
8105  case kExprLocalSet: {
8106  IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "local index",
8107  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8108  len = 1 + imm.length;
8109  optional.index = imm.index;
8110  break;
8111  }
8112  case kExprLocalTee: {
8113  IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "local index",
8114  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8115  len = 1 + imm.length;
8116  optional.index = imm.index;
8117  break;
8118  }
8119  case kExprGlobalGet: {
8120  GlobalIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8121  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8122  len = 1 + imm.length;
8123  optional.index = imm.index;
8124  break;
8125  }
8126  case kExprGlobalSet: {
8127  GlobalIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8128  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8129  len = 1 + imm.length;
8130  optional.index = imm.index;
8131  break;
8132  }
8133  case kExprTableGet: {
8134  IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "table index",
8135  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8136  len = 1 + imm.length;
8137  optional.index = imm.index;
8138  break;
8139  }
8140  case kExprTableSet: {
8141  IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "table index",
8142  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8143  len = 1 + imm.length;
8144  optional.index = imm.index;
8145  break;
8146  }
8147 
8148 #define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
8149  case kExpr##name: { \
8150  MemoryAccessImmediate imm( \
8151  &decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), sizeof(ctype), \
8152  Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8153  len = 1 + imm.length; \
8154  optional.offset = imm.offset; \
8155  break; \
8156  }
8157  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8S, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
8158  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);
8159  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16S, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
8160  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);
8161  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8S, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
8162  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
8163  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
8164  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
8165  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
8166  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);
8167  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
8168  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
8169  LOAD_CASE(F32LoadMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
8170  LOAD_CASE(F64LoadMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
8171 #undef LOAD_CASE
8172 
8173 #define STORE_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
8174  case kExpr##name: { \
8175  MemoryAccessImmediate imm( \
8176  &decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), sizeof(ctype), \
8177  Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8178  len = 1 + imm.length; \
8179  optional.offset = imm.offset; \
8180  break; \
8181  }
8182  STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem8, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
8183  STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem16, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
8184  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem8, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
8185  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem16, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
8186  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem32, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
8187  STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
8188  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
8189  STORE_CASE(F32StoreMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
8190  STORE_CASE(F64StoreMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
8191 #undef STORE_CASE
8192 
8193  case kExprMemorySize: {
8194  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8195  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8196  len = 1 + imm.length;
8197  break;
8198  }
8199  case kExprMemoryGrow: {
8200  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8201  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8202  len = 1 + imm.length;
8203  break;
8204  }
8205  case kExprI32Const: {
8206  ImmI32Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8207  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8208  len = 1 + imm.length;
8209  optional.i32 = imm.value;
8210  break;
8211  }
8212  case kExprI64Const: {
8213  ImmI64Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8214  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8215  len = 1 + imm.length;
8216  optional.i64 = imm.value;
8217  break;
8218  }
8219  case kExprF32Const: {
8220  ImmF32Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8221  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8222  len = 1 + imm.length;
8223  optional.f32 = imm.value;
8224  break;
8225  }
8226  case kExprF64Const: {
8227  ImmF64Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8228  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8229  len = 1 + imm.length;
8230  optional.f64 = imm.value;
8231  break;
8232  }
8233 
8234 #define EXECUTE_BINOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \
8235  case kExpr##name: \
8236  break;
8237 
8238  FOREACH_COMPARISON_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8239  FOREACH_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8240  FOREACH_TRAPPING_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8241  FOREACH_MORE_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8242 #undef EXECUTE_BINOP
8243 
8244 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \
8245  case kExpr##name: \
8246  break;
8247 
8248  FOREACH_SIMPLE_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8249 #undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8250 
8251 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \
8252  to_reg) \
8253  case kExpr##name: \
8254  break;
8255 
8256  FOREACH_ADDITIONAL_CONVERT_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8257  FOREACH_CONVERT_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8258  FOREACH_REINTERPRET_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8259 #undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8260 
8261 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, to_ctype, to_type, op) \
8262  case kExpr##name: \
8263  break;
8264 
8265  FOREACH_BITS_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8266 #undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8267 
8268 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, to_ctype, to_type) \
8269  case kExpr##name: \
8270  break;
8271 
8272  FOREACH_EXTENSION_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8273 #undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8274 
8275  case kExprRefNull: {
8276  HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &detected, &decoder,
8277  wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8278  value_type_reader::Populate(&imm.type, module_);
8279  optional.ref_type_bit_field = imm.type.raw_bit_field();
8280  len = 1 + imm.length;
8281  break;
8282  }
8283  case kExprRefIsNull:
8284  case kExprRefEq:
8285  case kExprRefAsNonNull: {
8286  len = 1;
8287  break;
8288  }
8289  case kExprRefFunc: {
8290  IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "function index",
8291  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8292  optional.index = imm.index;
8293  len = 1 + imm.length;
8294  break;
8295  }
8296 
8297  case kGCPrefix:
8298  DecodeGCOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8299  break;
8300 
8301  case kNumericPrefix:
8302  DecodeNumericOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8303  break;
8304 
8305  case kAtomicPrefix:
8306  DecodeAtomicOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8307  break;
8308 
8309  case kSimdPrefix: {
8310  bool is_valid_simd_op =
8311  DecodeSimdOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8312  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!is_valid_simd_op)) {
8313  UNREACHABLE();
8314  }
8315  break;
8316  }
8317 
8318  case kExprCallRef:
8319  case kExprReturnCallRef: {
8320  SigIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8321  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8322  optional.index = imm.index.index;
8323  len = 1 + imm.length;
8324  break;
8325  }
8326 
8327  default:
8328  // Not implemented yet
8329  UNREACHABLE();
8330  }
8331 
8332  return WasmInstruction{orig, opcode, len, static_cast<uint32_t>(pc),
8333  optional};
8334 }
8335 
8336 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeGCOp(WasmOpcode opcode,
8337  WasmInstruction::Optional* optional,
8338  Decoder* decoder, InterpreterCode* code,
8339  pc_t pc, int* const len) {
8340  WasmDetectedFeatures detected;
8341  switch (opcode) {
8342  case kExprStructNew:
8343  case kExprStructNewDefault: {
8344  StructIndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8345  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8346  optional->index = imm.index.index;
8347  *len += imm.length;
8348  break;
8349  }
8350  case kExprStructGet:
8351  case kExprStructGetS:
8352  case kExprStructGetU:
8353  case kExprStructSet: {
8354  FieldImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8355  optional->gc_field_immediate = {imm.struct_imm.index.index,
8356  imm.field_imm.index};
8357  *len += imm.length;
8358  break;
8359  }
8360  case kExprArrayNew:
8361  case kExprArrayNewDefault:
8362  case kExprArrayGet:
8363  case kExprArrayGetS:
8364  case kExprArrayGetU:
8365  case kExprArraySet:
8366  case kExprArrayFill: {
8367  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8368  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8369  optional->index = imm.index.index;
8370  *len += imm.length;
8371  break;
8372  }
8373 
8374  case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
8375  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8376  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8377  optional->gc_array_new_fixed.array_index = array_imm.index.index;
8378  *len += array_imm.length;
8379  IndexImmediate data_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "array length",
8380  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8381  optional->gc_array_new_fixed.length = data_imm.index;
8382  *len += data_imm.length;
8383  break;
8384  }
8385 
8386  case kExprArrayNewData:
8387  case kExprArrayNewElem:
8388  case kExprArrayInitData:
8389  case kExprArrayInitElem: {
8390  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8391  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8392  optional->gc_array_new_or_init_data.array_index = array_imm.index.index;
8393  *len += array_imm.length;
8394  IndexImmediate data_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "segment index",
8395  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8396  optional->gc_array_new_or_init_data.data_index = data_imm.index;
8397  *len += data_imm.length;
8398  break;
8399  }
8400 
8401  case kExprArrayCopy: {
8402  ArrayIndexImmediate dest_array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8403  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8404  optional->gc_array_copy.dest_array_index = dest_array_imm.index.index;
8405  *len += dest_array_imm.length;
8406  ArrayIndexImmediate src_array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8407  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8408  optional->gc_array_copy.src_array_index = src_array_imm.index.index;
8409  *len += src_array_imm.length;
8410  break;
8411  }
8412 
8413  case kExprRefI31:
8414  case kExprI31GetS:
8415  case kExprI31GetU:
8416  case kExprAnyConvertExtern:
8417  case kExprExternConvertAny:
8418  case kExprArrayLen:
8419  break;
8420 
8421  case kExprRefCast:
8422  case kExprRefCastNull:
8423  case kExprRefTest:
8424  case kExprRefTestNull: {
8425  HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &detected, decoder,
8426  code->at(pc + *len), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8427  value_type_reader::Populate(&imm.type, module_);
8428  optional->gc_heap_type_immediate.length = imm.length;
8429  optional->gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field =
8430  imm.type.raw_bit_field();
8431  *len += imm.length;
8432  break;
8433  }
8434 
8435  case kExprBrOnCast:
8436  case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
8437  BrOnCastImmediate flags_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8438  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8439  *len += flags_imm.length;
8440  BranchDepthImmediate branch(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8441  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8442  *len += branch.length;
8443  HeapTypeImmediate source_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &detected,
8444  decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8445  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8446  value_type_reader::Populate(&source_imm.type, module_);
8447  *len += source_imm.length;
8448  HeapTypeImmediate target_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &detected,
8449  decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8450  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8451  value_type_reader::Populate(&target_imm.type, module_);
8452  *len += target_imm.length;
8453  DCHECK(target_imm.type.raw_bit_field() <
8454  (1 << kBranchOnCastDataTargetTypeBitSize));
8455  optional->br_on_cast_data = BranchOnCastData{
8456  branch.depth, flags_imm.flags.src_is_null,
8457  flags_imm.flags.res_is_null, target_imm.type.raw_bit_field()};
8458  break;
8459  }
8460 
8461  default:
8462  FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s", code->start[pc],
8463  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(code->start[pc])));
8464  UNREACHABLE();
8465  }
8466 }
8467 
8468 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeNumericOp(WasmOpcode opcode,
8469  WasmInstruction::Optional* optional,
8470  Decoder* decoder,
8471  InterpreterCode* code, pc_t pc,
8472  int* const len) {
8473  switch (opcode) {
8474 #define DECODE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \
8475  to_reg) \
8476  case kExpr##name: \
8477  break;
8478 
8479  FOREACH_TRUNCSAT_UNOP(DECODE_UNOP)
8480 #undef DECODE_UNOP
8481 
8482  case kExprMemoryInit: {
8483  MemoryInitImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8484  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8485  DCHECK_LT(imm.data_segment.index, module_->num_declared_data_segments);
8486  optional->index = imm.data_segment.index;
8487  *len += imm.length;
8488  break;
8489  }
8490  case kExprDataDrop: {
8491  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "data segment index",
8492  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8493  DCHECK_LT(imm.index, module_->num_declared_data_segments);
8494  optional->index = imm.index;
8495  *len += imm.length;
8496  break;
8497  }
8498  case kExprMemoryCopy: {
8499  MemoryCopyImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8500  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8501  *len += imm.length;
8502  break;
8503  }
8504  case kExprMemoryFill: {
8505  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8506  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8507  *len += imm.length;
8508  break;
8509  }
8510  case kExprTableInit: {
8511  TableInitImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8512  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8513  optional->table_init.table_index = imm.table.index;
8514  optional->table_init.element_segment_index = imm.element_segment.index;
8515  *len += imm.length;
8516  break;
8517  }
8518  case kExprElemDrop: {
8519  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "element segment index",
8520  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8521  optional->index = imm.index;
8522  *len += imm.length;
8523  break;
8524  }
8525  case kExprTableCopy: {
8526  TableCopyImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8527  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8528  optional->table_copy.dst_table_index = imm.table_dst.index;
8529  optional->table_copy.src_table_index = imm.table_src.index;
8530  *len += imm.length;
8531  break;
8532  }
8533  case kExprTableGrow: {
8534  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "table index",
8535  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8536  optional->index = imm.index;
8537  *len += imm.length;
8538  break;
8539  }
8540  case kExprTableSize: {
8541  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "table index",
8542  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8543  optional->index = imm.index;
8544  *len += imm.length;
8545  break;
8546  }
8547  case kExprTableFill: {
8548  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "table index",
8549  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8550  optional->index = imm.index;
8551  *len += imm.length;
8552  break;
8553  }
8554  default:
8555  FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s", code->start[pc],
8556  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(code->start[pc])));
8557  UNREACHABLE();
8558  }
8559 }
8560 
8561 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeAtomicOp(WasmOpcode opcode,
8562  WasmInstruction::Optional* optional,
8563  Decoder* decoder,
8564  InterpreterCode* code, pc_t pc,
8565  int* const len) {
8566  switch (opcode) {
8567  case kExprAtomicNotify:
8568  case kExprI32AtomicWait: {
8569  MachineType memtype = MachineType::Uint32();
8570  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8571  ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()),
8572  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8573  optional->offset = imm.offset;
8574  *len += imm.length;
8575  break;
8576  }
8577  case kExprI64AtomicWait: {
8578  MachineType memtype = MachineType::Uint64();
8579  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8580  ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()),
8581  Decoder::kNoValidation);
8582  optional->offset = imm.offset;
8583  *len += imm.length;
8584  break;
8585  }
8586  case kExprAtomicFence:
8587  *len += 1;
8588  break;
8589 
8590 #define ATOMIC_BINOP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type, operation) \
8591  case kExpr##name: { \
8592  MachineType memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
8593  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), \
8594  ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()), \
8595  Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8596  optional->offset = imm.offset; \
8597  *len += imm.length; \
8598  break; \
8599  }
8600  FOREACH_ATOMIC_BINOP(ATOMIC_BINOP)
8601 #undef ATOMIC_BINOP
8602 
8603 #define ATOMIC_OP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type) \
8604  case kExpr##name: { \
8605  MachineType memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
8606  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), \
8607  ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()), \
8608  Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8609  optional->offset = imm.offset; \
8610  *len += imm.length; \
8611  break; \
8612  }
8613  FOREACH_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP(ATOMIC_OP)
8614  FOREACH_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(ATOMIC_OP)
8615  FOREACH_ATOMIC_STORE_OP(ATOMIC_OP)
8616 #undef ATOMIC_OP
8617 
8618  default:
8619  FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s", code->start[pc],
8620  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(code->start[pc])));
8621  UNREACHABLE();
8622  }
8623 }

8688 // static
8689 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PrintBytecodeCompressionStats() {
8690  size_t total_bytecode_size = std::atomic_load(&total_bytecode_size_);
8691  printf("Total bytecode size: %zu bytes.\n", total_bytecode_size);
8692  size_t space_saved_in_bytes =
8693  2 * std::atomic_load(&emitted_short_slot_offset_count_) +
8694  4 * std::atomic_load(&emitted_short_memory_offset_count_);
8695  double saved_pct = (total_bytecode_size + space_saved_in_bytes == 0)
8696  ? .0
8697  : 100.0 * space_saved_in_bytes /
8698  (total_bytecode_size + space_saved_in_bytes);
8699  printf("Bytes saved: %zu (%.1f%%).\n", space_saved_in_bytes, saved_pct);
8700 }
8701 
8702 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(const FunctionSig* sig,
8703  bool is_indirect_call) {
8704  size_t stack_index;
8705  if (is_indirect_call) {
8706  // Subtract one to discard the function index on the top of the stack.
8707  DCHECK_LE(sig->parameter_count(), stack_.size() - 1);
8708  stack_index = stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count() - 1;
8709  } else {
8710  DCHECK_LE(sig->parameter_count(), stack_.size());
8711  stack_index = stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count();
8712  }
8713 
8714  bool fast_path = sig->parameter_count() > 1 && sig->parameter_count() < 32 &&
8715  !WasmBytecode::HasRefOrSimdArgs(sig);
8716  if (fast_path) {
8717  if (sig->parameter_count() == 2) {
8718  const ValueType type0 = sig->GetParam(0);
8719  const ValueKind kind0 = type0.kind();
8720  ValueType type1 = sig->GetParam(1);
8721  const ValueKind kind1 = type1.kind();
8722  uint32_t to = CreateSlot(type0);
8723  CreateSlot(type1);
8724 
8725  uint32_t copyslot32_two_args_func_id =
8726  ((kind0 == kI64 || kind0 == kF64) ? 0x01 : 0x00) |
8727  ((kind1 == kI64 || kind1 == kF64) ? 0x02 : 0x00);
8728  static const InstructionHandler kCopySlot32TwoArgFuncs[4] = {
8729  k_s2s_CopySlot_ll, k_s2s_CopySlot_lq, k_s2s_CopySlot_ql,
8730  k_s2s_CopySlot_qq};
8731 
8732  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
8733  EmitFnId(kCopySlot32TwoArgFuncs[copyslot32_two_args_func_id]);
8734  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to].slot_offset);
8735  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
8736  stack_index++;
8737  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
8738  stack_index++;
8739  }
8740  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
8741  } else {
8742  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(s2s_CopySlotMulti) {
8743  EmitI32Const(static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->parameter_count()));
8744 
8745  uint32_t arg_size_mask = 0;
8746  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
8747  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(index);
8748  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
8749  if (kind == kI64 || kind == kF64) {
8750  arg_size_mask |= (1 << index);
8751  }
8752  }
8753  EmitI32Const(arg_size_mask);
8754 
8755  uint32_t to = 0;
8756  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
8757  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(index);
8758  to = CreateSlot(value_type);
8759  if (index == 0) {
8760  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to].slot_offset);
8761  }
8762  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
8763  stack_index++;
8764  }
8765  }
8766  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
8767  }
8768  } else {
8769  // Slow path.
8770  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
8771  ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(index);
8772  uint32_t to = CreateSlot(value_type);
8773  EmitCopySlot(value_type, stack_[stack_index], to);
8774  stack_index++;
8775  }
8776  }
8777 }
8778 
8779 // static
8780 void WasmInterpreter::NotifyIsolateDisposal(Isolate* isolate) {
8781  WasmInterpreterThread::NotifyIsolateDisposal(isolate);
8782 }
8783 
8784 // Checks if {obj} is a subtype of type, thus checking will always
8785 // succeed.
8786 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(ValueType obj_type,
8787  HeapType type) const {
8788  return IsSubtypeOf(obj_type, ValueType::RefNull(type), module_);
8789 }
8790 
8791 // Returns true if type checking will always fail, either because the types
8792 // are unrelated or because the target_type is one of the null sentinels and
8793 // conversion to null does not succeed.
8794 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::TypeCheckAlwaysFails(ValueType obj_type,
8795  HeapType expected_type,
8796  bool null_succeeds) const {
8797  bool types_unrelated =
8798  !IsSubtypeOf(ValueType::Ref(expected_type), obj_type, module_) &&
8799  !IsSubtypeOf(obj_type, ValueType::RefNull(expected_type), module_);
8800  // (Comment copied from function-body-decoder-impl.h).
8801  // For "unrelated" types the check can still succeed for the null value on
8802  // instructions treating null as a successful check.
8803  // TODO(12868): For string views, this implementation anticipates that
8804  // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40 will be resolved
8805  // by making the views standalone types.
8806  return (types_unrelated &&
8807  (!null_succeeds || !obj_type.is_nullable() ||
8808  obj_type.is_string_view() || expected_type.is_string_view())) ||
8809  (!null_succeeds &&
8810  (expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNone ||
8811  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoFunc ||
8812  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExtern));
8813 }
