9322 
9323 RegMode WasmBytecodeGenerator::EncodeInstruction(const WasmInstruction& instr,
9324  RegMode curr_reg_mode,
9325  RegMode next_reg_mode) {
9326  if (!v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
9327  DCHECK_EQ(handler_size_, InstrHandlerSize::Large);
9328  return DoEncodeInstruction(instr, curr_reg_mode, next_reg_mode);
9329  }
9330 
9331  size_t current_instr_code_offset = code_.size();
9332  size_t current_slots_size = slots_.size();
9333  current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
9334  handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Small;
9335  stack_.clear_history();
9336 
9337  RegMode reg_mode = DoEncodeInstruction(instr, curr_reg_mode, next_reg_mode);
9338  if (current_instr_encoding_failed_) {
9339  DCHECK(!HasSideEffects(instr.opcode));
9340  code_.resize(current_instr_code_offset);
9341  slots_.resize(current_slots_size);
9342  stack_.rollback();
9343  current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
9344  handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Large;
9345  reg_mode = DoEncodeInstruction(instr, curr_reg_mode, next_reg_mode);
9346  DCHECK(!current_instr_encoding_failed_);
9347  }
9348 
9349  return reg_mode;
9350 }
9351 
9352 RegMode WasmBytecodeGenerator::DoEncodeInstruction(const WasmInstruction& instr,
9353  RegMode curr_reg_mode,
9354  RegMode next_reg_mode) {
9355  DCHECK(curr_reg_mode != RegMode::kAnyReg);
9356 
9357 #ifdef DEBUG
9358  was_current_instruction_reachable_ = is_instruction_reachable_;
9359 #endif // DEBUG
9360  if (!is_instruction_reachable_) {
9361  if (instr.opcode == kExprBlock || instr.opcode == kExprLoop ||
9362  instr.opcode == kExprIf || instr.opcode == kExprTry) {
9363  unreachable_block_count_++;
9364  } else if (instr.opcode == kExprEnd || instr.opcode == kExprDelegate) {
9365  DCHECK_GT(unreachable_block_count_, 0);
9366  if (0 == --unreachable_block_count_) {
9367  is_instruction_reachable_ = true;
9368  }
9369  } else if (instr.opcode == kExprElse || instr.opcode == kExprCatch ||
9370  instr.opcode == kExprCatchAll) {
9371  if (1 == unreachable_block_count_) {
9372  is_instruction_reachable_ = true;
9373  unreachable_block_count_ = 0;
9374  }
9375  }
9376  }
9377  if (!is_instruction_reachable_) return RegMode::kNoReg;
9378 
9379  ValueKind top_stack_slot_type = GetTopStackType(curr_reg_mode);
9380 
9381  OperatorMode mode = kS2S;
9382  if (v8_flags.drumbrake_register_optimization) {
9383  switch (next_reg_mode) {
9384  case RegMode::kNoReg:
9385  if (curr_reg_mode != RegMode::kNoReg) {
9386  mode = kR2S;
9387  }
9388  break;
9389  case RegMode::kAnyReg:
9390  default: // kI32Reg|kI64Reg|kF32Reg|kF64Reg
9391  if (curr_reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
9392  if (ToRegisterIsAllowed(instr)) {
9393  mode = kS2R;
9394  } else {
9395  mode = kS2S;
9396  }
9397  } else {
9398  if (ToRegisterIsAllowed(instr)) {
9399  mode = kR2R;
9400  } else {
9401  mode = kR2S;
9402  }
9403  }
9404  break;
9405  }
9406  }
9407 
9408 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
9409  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_bytecode_generator) {
9410  printf("PRE @%-3u: %-24s: %3s %-7s -> %-7s\n", instr.pc,
9411  wasm::WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(instr.opcode)),
9412  GetOperatorModeString(mode), GetRegModeString(curr_reg_mode),
9413  GetRegModeString(next_reg_mode));
9414  }
9415 
9416  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
9417  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_TraceInstruction);
9418  EmitI32Const(instr.pc);
9419  EmitI32Const(instr.opcode);
9420  EmitI32Const(static_cast<int>(curr_reg_mode));
9421  }
9422 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
9423 
9424  switch (instr.opcode) {
9425  case kExprUnreachable: {
9426  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Unreachable, instr.pc);
9427  SetUnreachableMode();
9428  break;
9429  }
9430  case kExprNop:
9431  break;
9432  case kExprBlock:
9433  case kExprLoop: {
9434  PreserveArgsAndLocals();
9435  BeginBlock(instr.opcode, instr.optional.block);
9436  break;
9437  }
9438  case kExprTry: {
9439  PreserveArgsAndLocals();
9440  int parent_or_matching_try_block_index = GetCurrentTryBlockIndex(true);
9441  int ancestor_try_block_index = GetCurrentTryBlockIndex(false);
9442  int try_block_index = BeginBlock(instr.opcode, instr.optional.block);
9443  eh_data_.AddTryBlock(try_block_index, parent_or_matching_try_block_index,
9444  ancestor_try_block_index);
9445  break;
9446  }
9447  case kExprIf: {
9448  PreserveArgsAndLocals();
9449  if (mode == kR2S) {
9450  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_If);
9451  } else {
9452  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9453  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_If);
9454  I32Pop(); // cond
9455  }
9456  BeginBlock(instr.opcode, instr.optional.block);
9457  EmitIfElseBranchOffset();
9458  break;
9459  }
9460  case kExprElse: {
9461  DCHECK_GT(current_block_index_, 0);
9462  DCHECK(blocks_[current_block_index_].IsIf());
9463  BeginElseBlock(current_block_index_, false);
9464  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Else);
9465  EmitIfElseBranchOffset(); // Jumps to the end of the 'else' block.
9466  break;
9467  }
9468  case kExprCatch:
9469  case kExprCatchAll: {
9470  DCHECK_GT(current_block_index_, 0);
9471 
9472  int try_block_index = eh_data_.GetCurrentTryBlockIndex();
9473  DCHECK_GT(try_block_index, 0);
9474 
9475  EndBlock(instr.opcode); // End previous try or catch.
9476 
9477  stack_.resize(blocks_[try_block_index].stack_size_);
9478  int32_t catch_block_index =
9479  BeginBlock(instr.opcode, blocks_[try_block_index].signature_);
9480 
9481  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Catch);
9482  EmitTryCatchBranchOffset(); // Jumps to the end of the try/catch blocks.
9483 
9484  uint32_t first_param_slot_index = UINT_MAX;
9485  uint32_t first_ref_param_slot_index = UINT_MAX;
9486  if (instr.opcode == kExprCatch) {
9487  // Exception arguments are pushed into the stack.
9488  const WasmTag& tag = module_->tags[instr.optional.index];
9489  const FunctionSig* sig = tag.sig;
9490  for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
9491  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(i);
9492  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
9493  switch (kind) {
9494  case kI32:
9495  case kI64:
9496  case kF32:
9497  case kF64:
9498  case kS128:
9499  case kRef:
9500  case kRefNull: {
9501  uint32_t slot_index = CreateSlot(value_type);
9502  if (first_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX) {
9503  first_param_slot_index = slot_index;
9504  }
9505  if ((kind == kRefNull || kind == kRef) &&
9506  first_ref_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX) {
9507  first_ref_param_slot_index = slot_index;
9508  }
9509  PushSlot(slot_index);
9510  slots_[slot_index].value_type = value_type;
9511  break;
9512  }
9513  default:
9514  UNREACHABLE();
9515  }
9516  }
9517  }
9518 
9519  blocks_[catch_block_index].first_block_index_ =
9520  blocks_[try_block_index].first_block_index_;
9521 
9522  if (instr.opcode == kExprCatch) {
9523  eh_data_.AddCatchBlock(
9524  current_block_index_, instr.optional.index,
9525  first_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX
9526  ? 0
9527  : slots_[first_param_slot_index].slot_offset,
9528  first_ref_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX
9529  ? 0
9530  : slots_[first_ref_param_slot_index].ref_stack_index,
9531  static_cast<int>(code_.size()));
9532  } else { // kExprCatchAll
9533  eh_data_.AddCatchBlock(current_block_index_,
9534  WasmEHData::kCatchAllTagIndex, 0, 0,
9535  static_cast<int>(code_.size()));
9536  }
9537 
9538  break;
9539  }
9540  case kExprDelegate: {
9541  int32_t target_block_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth + 1);
9542  DCHECK_LT(target_block_index, blocks_.size());
9543  int32_t delegated_try_block_index = WasmEHData::kDelegateToCallerIndex;
9544  if (target_block_index > 0) {
9545  const BlockData& target_block = blocks_[target_block_index];
9546  delegated_try_block_index = target_block.IsTry()
9547  ? target_block_index
9548  : target_block.parent_try_block_index_;
9549  }
9550  eh_data_.AddDelegatedBlock(delegated_try_block_index);
9551  EndBlock(kExprDelegate);
9552  break;
9553  }
9554  case kExprThrow: {
9555  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Throw);
9556  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
9557 
9558  // Exception arguments are popped from the stack (in reverse order!)
9559  const WasmTag& tag = module_->tags[instr.optional.index];
9560  const WasmTagSig* sig = tag.sig;
9561  DCHECK_GE(stack_.size(), sig->parameter_count());
9562  size_t stack_index = stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count();
9563  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count();
9564  index++, stack_index++) {
9565  ValueKind kind = sig->GetParam(index).kind();
9566  DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(kind, slots_[stack_[stack_index]].kind()));
9567  switch (kind) {
9568  case kI32:
9569  case kI64:
9570  case kF32:
9571  case kF64:
9572  case kS128: {
9573  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
9574  break;
9575  }
9576  case kRef:
9577  case kRefNull: {
9578  uint32_t ref_index = slots_[stack_[stack_index]].ref_stack_index;
9579  Emit(&ref_index, sizeof(uint32_t));
9580  break;
9581  }
9582  default:
9583  UNREACHABLE();
9584  }
9585  }
9586 
9587  stack_.resize(stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count());
9588  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
9589  CurrentCodePos());
9590  SetUnreachableMode();
9591  break;
9592  }
9593  case kExprRethrow: {
9594  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Rethrow);
9595  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9596  DCHECK(blocks_[target_branch_index].IsCatch() ||
9597  blocks_[target_branch_index].IsCatchAll());
9598  Emit(&target_branch_index, sizeof(int32_t));
9599  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
9600  CurrentCodePos());
9601  SetUnreachableMode();
9602  break;
9603  }
9604  case kExprEnd: {
9605  // If there is an 'if...end' statement without an 'else' branch, create
9606  // a dummy else branch used to store results.
9607  if (blocks_[current_block_index_].IsIf()) {
9608  uint32_t if_block_index = current_block_index_;
9609  DCHECK(!blocks_[if_block_index].HasElseBranch());
9610  uint32_t params_count = ParamsCount(blocks_[if_block_index]);
9611  if (params_count > 0) {
9612  BeginElseBlock(if_block_index, true);
9613  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Else);
9614  EmitIfElseBranchOffset(); // Jumps to the end of the 'else' block.
9615  }
9616  }
9617 
9618  if (EndBlock(kExprEnd) < 0) {
9619  Return();
9620  }
9621  break;
9622  }
9623  case kExprBr: {
9624  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9625  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBr);
9626 
9627  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9628  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9629  SetUnreachableMode();
9630  break;
9631  }
9632  case kExprBrIf: {
9633  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9634  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9635  blocks_[target_branch_index];
9636  if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9637  if (mode == kR2S) {
9638  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BranchIf);
9639  } else {
9640  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9641  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchIf);
9642  I32Pop(); // condition
9643  }
9644  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9645  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9646  } else {
9647  if (mode == kR2S) {
9648  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BranchIfWithParams);
9649  } else {
9650  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9651  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchIfWithParams);
9652  I32Pop(); // condition
9653  }
9654 
9655  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9656  const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9657  Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9658 
9659  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9660 
9661  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9662  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9663 
9664  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9665  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9666  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9667  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9668  delta);
9669  }
9670  break;
9671  }
9672  case kExprBrOnNull: {
9673  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9674  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9675  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9676  blocks_[target_branch_index];
9677  if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9678  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9679  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9680  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9681  // Remove nullability.
9682  if (value_type.kind() == kRefNull) {
9683  value_type = ValueType::Ref(value_type.heap_type());
9684  }
9685  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9686  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9687  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9688  } else {
9689  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNullWithParams);
9690  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9691  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9692  // Remove nullability.
9693  if (value_type.kind() == kRefNull) {
9694  value_type = ValueType::Ref(value_type.heap_type());
9695  }
9696  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9697 
9698  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9699  const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9700  Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9701 
9702  uint32_t stack_top = stack_.back();
9703  RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9704 
9705  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9706 
9707  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9708  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9709 
9710  stack_.push_back(stack_top); // re-push non-null ref on top of stack
9711 
9712  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9713  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9714  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9715  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9716  delta);
9717  }
9718  break;
9719  }
9720  case kExprBrOnNonNull: {
9721  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9722  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9723  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9724  blocks_[target_branch_index];
9725  if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9726  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNonNull);
9727  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9728  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9729  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9730  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9731  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9732 
9733  RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9734  } else {
9735  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNonNullWithParams);
9736  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9737  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9738  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9739 
9740  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9741  const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9742  Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9743 
9744  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9745 
9746  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9747  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9748 
9749  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9750  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9751  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9752  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9753  delta);
9754 
9755  RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9756  }
9757  break;
9758  }
9759  case kExprBrOnCast: {
9760  const BranchOnCastData& br_on_cast_data = instr.optional.br_on_cast_data;
9761  const int32_t target_branch_index =
9762  GetTargetBranch(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9763  bool null_succeeds = br_on_cast_data.res_is_null;
9764  const ValueType target_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
9765  HeapType::FromBits(br_on_cast_data.target_type_bit_fields),
9766  null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
9767 
9768  const ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
9769  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
9770 
9771  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions can
9772  // only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
9773  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
9774  TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type.heap_type()))) {
9775  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9776  // The branch will still not be taken on null if not {null_succeeds}.
9777  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
9778  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9779  RefPop(); // pop condition
9780  EmitRefValueType(obj_type.raw_bit_field());
9781  RefPush(target_type); // re-push condition value with a new HeapType.
9782  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9783  } else {
9784  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9785  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9786  }
9787  } else if (V8_LIKELY(!TypeCheckAlwaysFails(
9788  obj_type, target_type.heap_type(), null_succeeds))) {
9789  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnCast);
9790  EmitI32Const(null_succeeds);
9791  HeapType br_on_cast_data_target_type(
9792  HeapType::FromBits(br_on_cast_data.target_type_bit_fields));
9793  EmitI32Const(br_on_cast_data_target_type.is_index()
9794  ? br_on_cast_data_target_type.raw_bit_field()
9795  : target_type.heap_type().raw_bit_field());
9796  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
9797  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9798  RefPush(value_type);
9799  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9800  const uint32_t no_branch_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9801  Emit(&no_branch_code_offset, sizeof(no_branch_code_offset));
9802  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9803  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9804  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9805  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9806  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - no_branch_code_offset;
9807  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9808  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + no_branch_code_offset),
9809  delta);
9810  }
9811  break;
9812  }
9813  case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
9814  const BranchOnCastData& br_on_cast_data = instr.optional.br_on_cast_data;
9815  int32_t target_branch_index =
9816  GetTargetBranch(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9817  bool null_succeeds = br_on_cast_data.res_is_null;
9818  HeapType br_on_cast_data_target_type =
9819  HeapType::FromBits(br_on_cast_data.target_type_bit_fields);
9820  const ValueType target_type =
9821  ValueType::RefMaybeNull(br_on_cast_data_target_type,
9822  null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
9823 
9824  const ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
9825  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
9826 
9827  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions can
9828  // only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
9829  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type.heap_type(),
9830  null_succeeds))) {
9831  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9832  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9833  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9834  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(
9835  obj_type, target_type.heap_type()))) {
9836  // The branch can still be taken on null.
9837  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
9838  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index,
9839  kExprBrOnCast);
9840  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9841  RefPop(); // pop condition
9842  EmitRefValueType(obj_type.raw_bit_field());
9843  RefPush(target_type); // re-push condition value with a new HeapType.
9844  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9845  } else {
9846  // Fallthrough.
9847  }
9848  } else {
9849  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnCastFail);
9850  EmitI32Const(null_succeeds);
9851  EmitI32Const(br_on_cast_data_target_type.is_index()
9852  ? br_on_cast_data_target_type.raw_bit_field()
9853  : target_type.heap_type().raw_bit_field());
9854  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
9855  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9856  RefPush(value_type);
9857  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9858  const uint32_t no_branch_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9859  Emit(&no_branch_code_offset, sizeof(no_branch_code_offset));
9860  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9861  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9862  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9863  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9864  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - no_branch_code_offset;
9865  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9866  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + no_branch_code_offset),
9867  delta);
9868  }
9869  break;
9870  }
9871  case kExprBrTable: {
9872  if (mode == kR2S) {
9873  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BrTable);
9874  } else {
9875  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9876  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BrTable);
9877  I32Pop(); // branch label
9878  }
9879 
9880  // We emit the following bytecode for a br_table instruction:
9881  // s2s_BrTable handler id
9882  // (uint32) labels_count
9883  // (uint32) offset branch 0
9884  // (uint32) offset branch 1
9885  // ...
9886  // (uint32) offset branch labels_count - 1
9887  // (uint32) offset branch labels_count (default branch)
9888  // { Branch 0 slots }
9889  // { Branch 1 slots }
9890  // ...
9891  // { Branch labels_count slots }
9892  //
9893  // Where each {Branch i slots} contains the slots to execute a Branch
9894  // instruction:
9895  // { CopySlots for branch results, if present }
9896  // s2s_Branch handler id
9897  // (uint32) branch_offset (to be patched later)
9898  //
9899  const uint32_t labels_count = instr.optional.br_table.table_count;
9900  EmitI32Const(labels_count);
9901  uint32_t labels_offset_start = CurrentCodePos();
9902  for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= labels_count; i++) {
9903  // Here we don't know what will be the offset of this branch yet, so we
9904  // pass the current bytecode position as offset. This value will be
9905  // overwritten in the next loop.
9906  const uint32_t label_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9907  Emit(&label_offset, sizeof(label_offset));
9908  }
9909  for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= labels_count; i++) {
9910  uint32_t label =
9911  br_table_labels_[instr.optional.br_table.labels_index + i];
9912  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(label);
9913  uint32_t branch_code_start = CurrentCodePos();
9914  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrTable);
9915 
9916  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9917  EmitBranchTableOffset(label, CurrentCodePos());
9918 
9919  // Patch the branch offset with the correct jump offset.
9920  uint32_t label_offset = labels_offset_start + i * sizeof(uint32_t);
9921  int32_t delta = branch_code_start - label_offset;
9922  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9923  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + label_offset), delta);
9924  }
9925  SetUnreachableMode();
9926  break;
9927  }
9928  case kExprReturn: {
9929  Return();
9930  SetUnreachableMode();
9931  break;
9932  }
9933  case kExprCallFunction:
9934  case kExprReturnCall: {
9935  uint32_t function_index = instr.optional.index;
9936  const FunctionSig* sig = GetFunctionSignature(function_index);
9937 
9938  // Layout of a frame:
9939  // ------------------
9940  // stack slot #N-1 \
9941  // ... |
9942  // stack slot #0 _/
9943  // local #L-1 \
9944  // ... |
9945  // local #0 _/
9946  // const #C-1 \
9947  // ... |
9948  // const #0 _/
9949  // param #P-1 \
9950  // ... |
9951  // param #0 _/
9952  // return #R-1 \
9953  // ... |
9954  // return #0 _/
9955  // ------------------
9956 
9957  const bool is_imported = (module_->functions[function_index].imported);
9958  const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCall);
9959  uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
9960  uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
9961 
9962  std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
9963  rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
9964  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
9965  rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
9966  : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
9967  }
9968 
9969  InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, false);
9970 
9971  if (is_imported) {
9972  if (is_tail_call) {
9973  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallImportedFunction, instr.pc);
9974  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9975  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9976  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
9977  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
9978  } else {
9979  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallImportedFunction, instr.pc);
9980  }
9981  } else {
9982  if (is_tail_call) {
9983  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCall, instr.pc);
9984  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9985  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9986  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
9987  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
9988  } else {
9989  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallFunction, instr.pc);
9990  }
9991  }
9992  EmitI32Const(function_index);
9993  EmitStackIndex(static_cast<uint32_t>(stack_.size()));
9994  EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
9995  EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
9996 
9997  // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
9998  for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
9999  Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10000  }
10001 
10002 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10003  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10004  EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10005  ? 0
10006  : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10007  }
10008 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10009 
10010  if (!is_tail_call) {
10011  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10012  CurrentCodePos());
10013  }
10014 
10015  // Function results are pushed to the stack.
10016  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10017  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10018  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10019  switch (kind) {
10020  case kI32:
10021  case kI64:
10022  case kF32:
10023  case kF64:
10024  case kS128:
10025  case kRef:
10026  case kRefNull:
10027  PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10028  SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10029  break;
10030  default:
10031  UNREACHABLE();
10032  }
10033  }
10034 
10035  // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10036  // unreachable.
10037  if (is_tail_call) {
10038  SetUnreachableMode();
10039  }
10040 
10041  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10042  }
10043  case kExprCallIndirect:
10044  case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
10045  const FunctionSig* sig = module_->signature(
10046  ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.indirect_call.sig_index}));
10047 
10048  const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCallIndirect);
10049  uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
10050  uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
10051 
10052  // Reserve space for return values.
10053  std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
10054  rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
10055  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10056  rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
10057  : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
10058  }
10059 
10060  InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, true);
10061 
10062  bool is_table64 =
10063  module_->tables[instr.optional.indirect_call.table_index]
10064  .is_table64();
10065 
10066  if (is_tail_call) {
10067  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallIndirect,
10068  s2s_ReturnCallIndirect64, is_table64,
10069  instr.pc);
10070  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10071  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10072  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
10073  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
10074  } else {
10075  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallIndirect, s2s_CallIndirect64,
10076  is_table64, instr.pc);
10077  }
10078 
10079  // Pops the index of the function to call.
10080  is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
10081 
10082  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.indirect_call.table_index);
10083  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.indirect_call.sig_index);
10084 
10085  EmitStackIndex(stack_size());
10086  EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
10087  EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
10088 
10089  // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
10090  for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
10091  Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10092  }
10093 
10094 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10095  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10096  EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10097  ? 0
10098  : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10099  }
10100 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10101 
10102  if (!is_tail_call) {
10103  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10104  CurrentCodePos());
10105  }
10106 
10107  // Function result is pushed to the stack.
10108  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10109  ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10110  switch (value_type.kind()) {
10111  case kI32:
10112  case kI64:
10113  case kF32:
10114  case kF64:
10115  case kS128:
10116  case kRef:
10117  case kRefNull:
10118  PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10119  SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10120  break;
10121  default:
10122  UNREACHABLE();
10123  }
10124  }
10125 
10126  // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10127  // unreachable.
10128  if (is_tail_call) {
10129  SetUnreachableMode();
10130  }
10131 
10132  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10133  }
10134 
10135  case kExprCallRef:
10136  case kExprReturnCallRef: {
10137  const FunctionSig* sig =
10138  module_->signature(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index}));
10139  const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCallRef);
10140  uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
10141  uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
10142 
10143  // Reserve space for return values.
10144  std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
10145  rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
10146  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10147  rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
10148  : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
10149  }
10150 
10151  InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, true);
10152 
10153  if (is_tail_call) {
10154  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallRef, instr.pc);
10155  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10156  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10157  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
10158  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
10159  } else {
10160  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallRef, instr.pc);
10161  }
10162 
10163  // Pops the function to call.
10164  RefPop();
10165 
10166  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index); // Signature index.
10167  EmitStackIndex(stack_size());
10168  EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
10169  EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
10170 
10171  // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
10172  for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
10173  Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10174  }
10175 
10176 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10177  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10178  EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10179  ? 0
10180  : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10181  }
10182 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10183 
10184  if (!is_tail_call) {
10185  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10186  CurrentCodePos());
10187  }
10188 
10189  // Function result is pushed to the stack.
10190  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10191  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10192  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10193  switch (kind) {
10194  case kI32:
10195  case kI64:
10196  case kF32:
10197  case kF64:
10198  case kS128:
10199  case kRef:
10200  case kRefNull:
10201  PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10202  SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10203  break;
10204  default:
10205  UNREACHABLE();
10206  }
10207  }
10208 
10209  // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10210  // unreachable.
10211  if (is_tail_call) {
10212  SetUnreachableMode();
10213  }
10214 
10215  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10216  }
10217 
10218  case kExprDrop: {
10219  switch (top_stack_slot_type) {
10220  case kI32:
10221  switch (mode) {
10222  case kR2R:
10223  case kS2R:
10224  UNREACHABLE();
10225  case kR2S:
10226  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I32Drop);
10227  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10228  case kS2S:
10229  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32Drop);
10230  I32Pop();
10231  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10232  }
10233  break;
10234  case kI64:
10235  switch (mode) {
10236  case kR2R:
10237  case kS2R:
10238  UNREACHABLE();
10239  case kR2S:
10240  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I64Drop);
10241  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10242  case kS2S:
10243  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64Drop);
10244  I64Pop();
10245  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10246  }
10247  break;
10248  case kF32:
10249  switch (mode) {
10250  case kR2R:
10251  case kS2R:
10252  UNREACHABLE();
10253  case kR2S:
10254  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F32Drop);
10255  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10256  case kS2S:
10257  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32Drop);
10258  F32Pop();
10259  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10260  }
10261  break;
10262  case kF64:
10263  switch (mode) {
10264  case kR2R:
10265  case kS2R:
10266  UNREACHABLE();
10267  case kR2S:
10268  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F64Drop);
10269  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10270  case kS2S:
10271  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64Drop);
10272  F64Pop();
10273  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10274  }
10275  break;
10276  case kS128:
10277  switch (mode) {
10278  case kR2R:
10279  case kR2S:
10280  case kS2R:
10281  UNREACHABLE();
10282  case kS2S:
10283  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128Drop);
10284  S128Pop();
10285  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10286  }
10287  break;
10288  case kRef:
10289  case kRefNull:
10290  switch (mode) {
10291  case kR2R:
10292  case kS2R:
10293  UNREACHABLE();
10294  case kR2S:
10295  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_RefDrop);
10296  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10297  case kS2S:
10298  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefDrop);
10299  RefPop();
10300  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10301  }
10302  break;
10303  default:
10304  UNREACHABLE();
10305  }
10306  break;
10307  }
10308  case kExprSelect:
10309  case kExprSelectWithType: {
10310  DCHECK_GE(stack_size(), 2);
10311  switch (slots_[stack_[stack_size() - 2]].kind()) {
10312  case kI32:
10313  switch (mode) {
10314  case kR2R:
10315  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_I32Select);
10316  I32Pop(); // val2
10317  I32Pop(); // val1
10318  return RegMode::kI32Reg;
10319  case kR2S:
10320  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I32Select);
10321  I32Pop(); // val2
10322  I32Pop(); // val1
10323  I32Push(); // result
10324  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10325  case kS2R:
10326  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I32Select);
10327  I32Pop(); // condition
10328  I32Pop(); // val2
10329  I32Pop(); // val1
10330  return RegMode::kI32Reg;
10331  case kS2S:
10332  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32Select);
10333  I32Pop(); // condition
10334  I32Pop(); // val2
10335  I32Pop(); // val1
10336  I32Push(); // result
10337  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10338  }
10339  break;
10340  case kI64:
10341  switch (mode) {
10342  case kR2R:
10343  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_I64Select);
10344  I64Pop(); // val2
10345  I64Pop(); // val1
10346  return RegMode::kI64Reg;
10347  case kR2S:
10348  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I64Select);
10349  I64Pop(); // val2
10350  I64Pop(); // val1
10351  I64Push(); // result
10352  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10353  case kS2R:
10354  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I64Select);
10355  I32Pop(); // condition
10356  I64Pop(); // val2
10357  I64Pop(); // val1
10358  return RegMode::kI64Reg;
10359  case kS2S:
10360  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64Select);
10361  I32Pop(); // condition
10362  I64Pop();
10363  I64Pop();
10364  I64Push();
10365  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10366  }
10367  break;
10368  case kF32:
10369  switch (mode) {
10370  case kR2R:
10371  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_F32Select);
10372  F32Pop(); // val2
10373  F32Pop(); // val1
10374  return RegMode::kF32Reg;
10375  case kR2S:
10376  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F32Select);
10377  F32Pop(); // val2
10378  F32Pop(); // val1
10379  F32Push(); // result
10380  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10381  case kS2R:
10382  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F32Select);
10383  I32Pop(); // condition
10384  F32Pop(); // val2
10385  F32Pop(); // val1
10386  return RegMode::kF32Reg;
10387  case kS2S:
10388  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32Select);
10389  I32Pop(); // condition
10390  F32Pop();
10391  F32Pop();
10392  F32Push();
10393  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10394  }
10395  break;
10396  case kF64:
10397  switch (mode) {
10398  case kR2R:
10399  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_F64Select);
10400  F64Pop(); // val2
10401  F64Pop(); // val1
10402  return RegMode::kF64Reg;
10403  case kR2S:
10404  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F64Select);
10405  F64Pop(); // val2
10406  F64Pop(); // val1
10407  F64Push(); // result
10408  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10409  case kS2R:
10410  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F64Select);
10411  I32Pop(); // condition
10412  F64Pop(); // val2
10413  F64Pop(); // val1
10414  return RegMode::kF64Reg;
10415  case kS2S:
10416  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64Select);
10417  I32Pop(); // condition
10418  F64Pop();
10419  F64Pop();
10420  F64Push();
10421  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10422  }
10423  break;
10424  case kS128:
10425  switch (mode) {
10426  case kR2R:
10427  case kS2R:
10428  UNREACHABLE();
10429  case kR2S:
10430  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_S128Select);
10431  S128Pop();
10432  S128Pop();
10433  S128Push();
10434  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10435  case kS2S:
10436  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128Select);
10437  I32Pop(); // condition
10438  S128Pop();
10439  S128Pop();

10441  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10442  }
10443  break;
10444  case kRef:
10445  case kRefNull:
10446  switch (mode) {
10447  case kR2R:
10448  case kS2R:
10449  UNREACHABLE();
10450  case kR2S: {
10451  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_RefSelect);
10452  RefPop(); // val2

10454  RefPush(type); // result

10457  case kS2S: {
10458  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefSelect);
10459  I32Pop(); // condition
10460  RefPop();
10461  ValueType type = RefPop();
10462  RefPush(type);
10463  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10464  }

10469  }
10470  break;
10471  }
10472 
10473  case kExprLocalGet: {
10474  switch (slots_[stack_[instr.optional.index]].kind()) {
10475  case kI32:
10476  case kI64:
10477  case kF32:
10478  case kF64:
10479  case kS128:
10480  case kRef:
10481  case kRefNull:
10482  switch (mode) {
10483  case kR2R:
10484  case kR2S:
10485  case kS2R:
10486  UNREACHABLE();
10487  case kS2S:
10488  PushCopySlot(instr.optional.index);
10489  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10490  }
10491  break;
10492  default:
10493  UNREACHABLE();
10494  }
10495  break;
10496  }
10497  case kExprLocalSet: {
10498  DCHECK_LE(instr.optional.index, stack_size());
10499  // Validation ensures that the target slot type must be the same as the
10500  // stack top slot type.
10501  const ValueType value_type =
10502  slots_[stack_[instr.optional.index]].value_type;
10503  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10504  DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(kind, top_stack_slot_type));
10505  switch (kind) {
10506  case kI32:
10507  case kI64:
10508  case kF32:
10509  case kF64:
10510  switch (mode) {
10511  case kR2R:
10512  case kS2R:
10513  UNREACHABLE();
10514  case kR2S:
10515  CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, false, true);
10516  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10517  case kS2S:
10518  CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, false, false);
10519  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10520  }
10521  break;
10522  case kS128:
10523  switch (mode) {
10524  case kR2R:
10525  case kR2S:
10526  case kS2R:
10527  UNREACHABLE();
10528  case kS2S:
10529  CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, false, false);
10530  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10531  }
10532  break;
10533  case kRef:
10534  case kRefNull:
10535  switch (mode) {
10536  case kR2R:
10537  case kR2S:
10538  case kS2R:
10539  UNREACHABLE();
10540  case kS2S:
10541  CopyToSlotAndPop(slots_[stack_.back()].value_type,
10542  instr.optional.index, false, false);
10543  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10544  }
10545  break;
10546  default:
10547  UNREACHABLE();
10548  }
10549  break;
10550  }
10551  case kExprLocalTee: {
10552  DCHECK_LE(instr.optional.index, stack_size());
10553  // Validation ensures that the target slot type must be the same as the
10554  // stack top slot type.
10555  const ValueType value_type =
10556  slots_[stack_[instr.optional.index]].value_type;
10557  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10558  DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(kind, top_stack_slot_type));
10559  switch (kind) {
10560  case kI32:
10561  case kI64:
10562  case kF32:
10563  case kF64:
10564  switch (mode) {
10565  case kR2R:
10566  CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, true, true);
10567  return GetRegMode(value_type.kind());
10568  case kR2S:
10569  UNREACHABLE();
10570  case kS2R:
10571  UNREACHABLE();
10572  case kS2S:
10573  CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, true, false);
10574  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10575  }
10576  break;
10577  case kS128:
10578  switch (mode) {
10579  case kR2R:
10580  case kR2S:
10581  case kS2R:
10582  UNREACHABLE();
10583  case kS2S:
10584  CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, true, false);
10585  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10586  }
10587  break;
10588  case kRef:
10589  case kRefNull:
10590  switch (mode) {
10591  case kR2R:
10592  case kR2S:
10593  case kS2R:
10594  UNREACHABLE();
10595  case kS2S:
10596  CopyToSlotAndPop(slots_[stack_.back()].value_type,
10597  instr.optional.index, true, false);
10598  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10599  }
10600  break;
10601  default:
10602  UNREACHABLE();
10603  }
10604  break;
10605  }
10606  case kExprGlobalGet: {
10607  switch (GetGlobalType(instr.optional.index)) {
10608  case kI32:
10609  switch (mode) {
10610  case kR2R:
10611  case kR2S:
10612  UNREACHABLE();
10613  case kS2R:
10614  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I32GlobalGet);
10615  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10616  return RegMode::kI32Reg;
10617  case kS2S:
10618  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32GlobalGet);
10619  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10620  I32Push();
10621  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10622  }
10623  break;
10624  case kI64:
10625  switch (mode) {
10626  case kR2R:
10627  case kR2S:
10628  UNREACHABLE();
10629  case kS2R:
10630  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I64GlobalGet);
10631  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10632  return RegMode::kI64Reg;
10633  case kS2S:
10634  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64GlobalGet);
10635  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10636  I64Push();
10637  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10638  }
10639  break;
10640  case kF32:
10641  switch (mode) {
10642  case kR2R:
10643  case kR2S:
10644  UNREACHABLE();
10645  case kS2R:
10646  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F32GlobalGet);
10647  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10648  return RegMode::kF32Reg;
10649  case kS2S:
10650  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32GlobalGet);
10651  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10652  F32Push();
10653  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10654  }
10655  break;
10656  case kF64:
10657  switch (mode) {
10658  case kR2R:
10659  case kR2S:
10660  UNREACHABLE();
10661  case kS2R:
10662  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F64GlobalGet);
10663  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10664  return RegMode::kF64Reg;
10665  case kS2S:
10666  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64GlobalGet);
10667  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10668  F64Push();
10669  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10670  }
10671  break;
10672  case kS128:
10673  switch (mode) {
10674  case kR2R:
10675  case kR2S:
10676  case kS2R:
10677  UNREACHABLE();
10678  case kS2S:
10679  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128GlobalGet);
10680  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10681  S128Push();
10682  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10683  }
10684  break;
10685  case kRef:
10686  case kRefNull:
10687  switch (mode) {
10688  case kR2R:
10689  case kR2S:
10690  case kS2R:
10691  UNREACHABLE();
10692  case kS2S:

10694  EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10695  RefPush(module_->globals[instr.optional.index].type);
10696  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10697  }
10698  break;
10699  default:
10700  UNREACHABLE();
10701  }
10702  break;
10703  }

10823 #define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
10824  case kExpr##name: { \
10825  switch (mode) { \
10826  case kR2R: \
10827  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2r_##name, r2r_##name##_Idx64, \
10828  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10829  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10830  return RegMode::k##type##Reg; \
10831  case kR2S: \
10832  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_##name, r2s_##name##_Idx64, \
10833  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10834  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10835  type##Push(); \
10836  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10837  case kS2R: \
10838  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2r_##name, s2r_##name##_Idx64, \
10839  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10840  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10841  MemIndexPop(); \
10842  return RegMode::k##type##Reg; \
10843  case kS2S: \
10844  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, s2s_##name##_Idx64, \
10845  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10846  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10847  MemIndexPop(); \
10848  type##Push(); \
10849  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10850  } \
10851  break; \
10852  }

10854  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);

10856  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);

10858  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
10859  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
10860  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
10861  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
10862  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);

11076 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \

11089  from_type##Pop(); \
11090  return RegMode::k##to_type##Reg; \
11091  case kS2S: \

11093  from_type##Pop(); \
11094  to_type##Push(); \
11095  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11096  } \
11097  break; \
11098  }

11105 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \
11106  to_reg) \
11107  case kExpr##name: { \
11108  switch (mode) { \
11109  case kR2R: \
11110  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2r_##name, instr.pc); \
11111  return RegMode::k##to_type##Reg; \
11112  case kR2S: \
11113  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_##name, instr.pc); \
11114  to_type##Push(); \
11115  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11116  case kS2R: \
11117  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2r_##name, instr.pc); \
11118  from_type##Pop(); \
11119  return RegMode::k##to_type##Reg; \
11120  case kS2S: \
11121  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, instr.pc); \
11122  from_type##Pop(); \
11123  to_type##Push(); \
11124  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11125  } \
11126  break; \
11127  }
11128  FOREACH_I64_CONVERT_FROM_FLOAT_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
11129  FOREACH_I32_CONVERT_FROM_FLOAT_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
11130 #undef EXECUTE_UNOP
11131 
11132 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, to_ctype, to_type, op) \
11133  case kExpr##name: { \
11134  switch (mode) { \
11135  case kR2R: \
11136  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_##name); \
11137  return RegMode::k##to_type##Reg; \
11138  case kR2S: \
11139  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_##name); \
11140  to_type##Push(); \
11141  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11142  case kS2R: \
11143  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_##name); \
11144  from_type##Pop(); \
11145  return RegMode::k##to_type##Reg; \
11146  case kS2S: \
11147  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_##name); \
11148  from_type##Pop(); \
11149  to_type##Push(); \
11150  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11151  } \
11152  break; \
11153  }
11154  FOREACH_BITS_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
11155 #undef EXECUTE_UNOP
11156 
11157 #define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, to_ctype, to_type) \
11158  case kExpr##name: { \
11159  switch (mode) { \
11160  case kR2R: \

11163  case kR2S: \

11165  to_type##Push(); \
11166  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11167  case kS2R: \
11168  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_##name); \
11169  from_type##Pop(); \
11170  return RegMode::k##to_type##Reg; \
11171  case kS2S: \
11172  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_##name); \
11173  from_type##Pop(); \
11174  to_type##Push(); \
11175  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11176  } \
11177  break; \
11178  }

11714  I32Pop(); // The value with which to fill the array.
11715  I32Pop(); // The offset at which to begin filling.
11716  RefPop(); // The array to fill.
11717  break;
11718  case kI16:
11719  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11720  I32Pop();
11721  I32Pop();
11722  I32Pop();
11723  RefPop();
11724  break;
11725  case kI32:
11726  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11727  I32Pop();
11728  I32Pop();
11729  I32Pop();
11730  RefPop();
11731  break;
11732  case kI64:
11733  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11734  I32Pop();
11735  I64Pop();
11736  I32Pop();
11737  RefPop();
11738  break;
11739  case kF32:
11740  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11741  I32Pop();
11742  F32Pop();
11743  I32Pop();
11744  RefPop();
11745  break;
11746  case kF64:
11747  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11748  I32Pop();
11749  F64Pop();
11750  I32Pop();
11751  RefPop();
11752  break;
11753  case kS128:
11754  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11755  I32Pop();
11756  S128Pop();
11757  I32Pop();
11758  RefPop();
11759  break;
11760  case kRef:
11761  case kRefNull:
11762  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefArrayFill, instr.pc);
11763  I32Pop();
11764  RefPop();
11765  I32Pop();
11766  RefPop();
11767  break;
11768  default:
11769  UNREACHABLE();
11770  }
11771  break;
11772  }
11773 
11774  case kExprRefI31: {
11775  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefI31);
11776  I32Pop();
11777  RefPush(ValueType::Ref(kWasmRefI31));
11778  break;
11779  }
11780 
11781  case kExprI31GetS: {
11782  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I31GetS, instr.pc);
11783  RefPop();
11784  I32Push();
11785  break;
11786  }
11787 
11788  case kExprI31GetU: {
11789  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I31GetU, instr.pc);
11790  RefPop();
11791  I32Push();
11792  break;
11793  }
11794 
11795  case kExprRefCast:
11796  case kExprRefCastNull: {
11797  bool null_succeeds = (instr.opcode == kExprRefCastNull);
11798  HeapType target_type = HeapType::FromBits(
11799  instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11800  ValueType resulting_value_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11801  target_type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
11802 
11803  ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
11804  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
11805 
11806  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
11807  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
11808  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type))) {
11809  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
11810  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AssertNotNullTypecheck, instr.pc);
11811  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11812  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11813  RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11814  } else {
11815  // Just forward the ref object.
11816  }
11817  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type,
11818  null_succeeds))) {
11819  // Unrelated types. The only way this will not trap is if the object
11820  // is null.
11821  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && null_succeeds) {
11822  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AssertNullTypecheck, instr.pc);
11823  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11824  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11825  RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11826  } else {
11827  // In this case we just trap.
11828  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TrapIllegalCast, instr.pc);
11829  }
11830  } else {
11831  if (instr.opcode == kExprRefCast) {
11832  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefCast, instr.pc);
11833  } else {
11834  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefCastNull, instr.pc);
11835  }
11836  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11837  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11838  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11839  RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11840  }
11841  break;
11842  }
11843 
11844  case kExprRefTest:
11845  case kExprRefTestNull: {
11846  bool null_succeeds = (instr.opcode == kExprRefTestNull);
11847  HeapType target_type = HeapType::FromBits(
11848  instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11849 
11850  ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
11851  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
11852 
11853  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
11854  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
11855  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type))) {
11856  // Type checking can still fail for null.
11857  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
11858  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefIsNonNull);
11859  RefPop();
11860  I32Push(); // bool
11861  } else {
11862  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestSucceeds);
11863  RefPop();
11864  I32Push(); // bool=true
11865  }
11866  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type,
11867  null_succeeds))) {
11868  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestFails);
11869  RefPop();
11870  I32Push(); // bool=false
11871  } else {
11872  if (instr.opcode == kExprRefTest) {
11873  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTest);
11874  } else {
11875  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestNull);
11876  }
11877  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11878  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11879  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11880  I32Push(); // bool
11881  }
11882  break;
11883  }
11884 
11885  case kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
11886  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AnyConvertExtern, instr.pc);
11887  ValueType extern_val = RefPop();
11888  ValueType intern_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11889  kWasmAnyRef, Nullability(extern_val.is_nullable()));
11890  RefPush(intern_type);
11891  break;
11892  }
11893 
11894  case kExprExternConvertAny: {
11895  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_ExternConvertAny);
11896  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11897  ValueType extern_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11898  kWasmExternRef, Nullability(value_type.is_nullable()));
11899  RefPush(extern_type);
11900  break;
11901  }
11902 
11903  case kExprMemoryInit:
11904  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_MemoryInit, s2s_Memory64Init,
11905  is_memory64_, instr.pc);
11906  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11907  I32Pop();
11908  I32Pop();
11909  MemIndexPop();
11910  break;
11911 
11912  case kExprDataDrop:
11913  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_DataDrop);
11914  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11915  break;
11916 
11917  case kExprMemoryCopy:
11918  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_MemoryCopy, s2s_Memory64Copy,
11919  is_memory64_, instr.pc);
11920  MemIndexPop();
11921  MemIndexPop();
11922  MemIndexPop();
11923  break;
11924 
11925  case kExprMemoryFill:
11926  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_MemoryFill, s2s_Memory64Fill,
11927  is_memory64_, instr.pc);
11928  MemIndexPop();
11929  I32Pop();
11930  MemIndexPop();
11931  break;
11932 
11933  case kExprTableInit: {
11934  bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11935  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableInit, s2s_Table64Init,
11936  is_table64, instr.pc);
11937 
11938  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_init.table_index);
11939  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_init.element_segment_index);
11940  I32Pop();
11941  I32Pop();
11942  is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11943  } break;
11944 
11945  case kExprElemDrop:
11946  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_ElemDrop);
11947  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11948  break;
11949 
11950  case kExprTableCopy: {
11951  bool is_src_table64 =
11952  module_->tables[instr.optional.table_copy.src_table_index]
11953  .is_table64();
11954  bool is_dst_table64 =
11955  module_->tables[instr.optional.table_copy.dst_table_index]
11956  .is_table64();
11957 
11958  if (is_src_table64) {
11959  if (is_dst_table64) {
11960  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Copy_64_64_64, instr.pc);
11961  } else {
11962  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Copy_32_64_32, instr.pc);
11963  }
11964  } else {
11965  if (is_dst_table64) {
11966  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Copy_64_32_32, instr.pc);
11967  } else {
11968  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableCopy, instr.pc);
11969  }
11970  }
11971  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_copy.dst_table_index);
11972  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_copy.src_table_index);
11973  is_dst_table64&& is_src_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11974  is_src_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11975  is_dst_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11976  } break;
11977 
11978  case kExprTableGrow: {
11979  bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11980  if (is_table64) {
11981  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Table64Grow);
11982  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11983  I64Pop();
11984  RefPop();
11985  I64Push();
11986  } else {
11987  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_TableGrow);
11988  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11989  I32Pop();
11990  RefPop();
11991  I32Push();
11992  }
11993  } break;
11994 
11995  case kExprTableSize: {
11996  bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11997  if (is_table64) {
11998  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Table64Size);
11999  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
12000  I64Push();
12001  } else {
12002  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_TableSize);
12003  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
12004  I32Push();
12005  }
12006  } break;
12007 
12008  case kExprTableFill: {
12009  bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
12010  if (is_table64) {
12011  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Fill, instr.pc);
12012  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
12013  I64Pop();
12014  RefPop();
12015  I64Pop();
12016  } else {
12017  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableFill, instr.pc);

12019  I32Pop();
12020  RefPop();
12021  I32Pop();
12022  }

12027  is_memory64_, instr.pc);

12504  double, base::saturated_cast<uint32_t>(a))
12505  CONVERT_CASE(F32x4DemoteF64x2Zero, float64x2, f64x2, float32x4, 2, 0,
12506  float, DoubleToFloat32(a))
12507  CONVERT_CASE(F64x2PromoteLowF32x4, float32x4, f32x4, float64x2, 2, 0,
12508  float, static_cast<double>(a))
12509 #undef CONVERT_CASE
12510 
12511 #define PACK_CASE(op, src_type, name, dst_type, count, dst_ctype) \
12512  case kExpr##op: { \
12513  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Simd##op); \
12514  S128Pop(); \
12515  S128Pop(); \
12516  S128Push(); \
12517  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12518  }
12519  PACK_CASE(I16x8SConvertI32x4, int32x4, i32x4, int16x8, 8, int16_t)
12520  PACK_CASE(I16x8UConvertI32x4, int32x4, i32x4, int16x8, 8, uint16_t)
12521  PACK_CASE(I8x16SConvertI16x8, int16x8, i16x8, int8x16, 16, int8_t)
12522  PACK_CASE(I8x16UConvertI16x8, int16x8, i16x8, int8x16, 16, uint8_t)
12523 #undef PACK_CASE
12524 
12525 #define SELECT_CASE(op) \
12526  case kExpr##op: { \
12527  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Simd##op); \
12528  S128Pop(); \
12529  S128Pop(); \
12530  S128Pop(); \
12531  S128Push(); \
12532  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12533  }
12534  SELECT_CASE(I8x16RelaxedLaneSelect)
12535  SELECT_CASE(I16x8RelaxedLaneSelect)
12536  SELECT_CASE(I32x4RelaxedLaneSelect)
12537  SELECT_CASE(I64x2RelaxedLaneSelect)
12538  SELECT_CASE(S128Select)
12539 #undef SELECT_CASE
12540 
12541  case kExprI32x4DotI16x8S: {
12542  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdI32x4DotI16x8S);
12543  S128Pop();
12544  S128Pop();
12545  S128Push();
12546  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12547  }
12548 
12549  case kExprS128Const: {
12550  PushConstSlot<Simd128>(
12551  simd_immediates_[instr.optional.simd_immediate_index]);
12552  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12553  }
12554 
12555  case kExprI16x8DotI8x16I7x16S: {
12556  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdI16x8DotI8x16I7x16S);
12557  S128Pop();
12558  S128Pop();
12559  S128Push();
12560  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12561  }
12562 
12563  case kExprI32x4DotI8x16I7x16AddS: {
12564  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdI32x4DotI8x16I7x16AddS);
12565  S128Pop();
12566  S128Pop();
12567  S128Pop();
12568  S128Push();
12569  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12570  }
12571 
12572  case kExprI8x16RelaxedSwizzle: {
12573  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdI8x16RelaxedSwizzle);
12574  S128Pop();
12575  S128Pop();
12576  S128Push();
12577  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12578  }
12579 
12580  case kExprI8x16Swizzle: {
12581  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdI8x16Swizzle);
12582  S128Pop();
12583  S128Pop();
12584  S128Push();
12585  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12586  }
12587 
12588  case kExprI8x16Shuffle: {
12589  uint32_t slot_index = CreateConstSlot(
12590  simd_immediates_[instr.optional.simd_immediate_index]);
12591 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
12592  TracePushConstSlot(slot_index);
12593 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
12594  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdI8x16Shuffle);
12595  PushSlot(slot_index);
12596  S128Pop();
12597  S128Pop();
12598  S128Pop();
12599  S128Push();
12600  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12601  }
12602 
12603  case kExprV128AnyTrue: {
12604  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_SimdV128AnyTrue);
12605  S128Pop();
12606  I32Push();
12607  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12608  }
12609 
12610 #define REDUCTION_CASE(op, name, stype, count, operation) \
12611  case kExpr##op: { \
12612  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Simd##op); \
12613  S128Pop(); \
12614  I32Push(); \
12615  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12616  }
12617  REDUCTION_CASE(I64x2AllTrue, i64x2, int64x2, 2, &)
12618  REDUCTION_CASE(I32x4AllTrue, i32x4, int32x4, 4, &)
12619  REDUCTION_CASE(I16x8AllTrue, i16x8, int16x8, 8, &)
12620  REDUCTION_CASE(I8x16AllTrue, i8x16, int8x16, 16, &)
12621 #undef REDUCTION_CASE
12622 
12623 #define QFM_CASE(op, name, stype, count, operation) \
12624  case kExpr##op: { \
12625  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Simd##op); \
12626  S128Pop(); \
12627  S128Pop(); \
12628  S128Pop(); \
12629  S128Push(); \
12630  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12631  }
12632  QFM_CASE(F32x4Qfma, f32x4, float32x4, 4, +)
12633  QFM_CASE(F32x4Qfms, f32x4, float32x4, 4, -)
12634  QFM_CASE(F64x2Qfma, f64x2, float64x2, 2, +)
12635  QFM_CASE(F64x2Qfms, f64x2, float64x2, 2, -)
12636 #undef QFM_CASE
12637 
12638 #define LOAD_SPLAT_CASE(op) \
