12640  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC( \
12641  s2s_SimdS128##op, s2s_SimdS128##op##_Idx64, is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
12642  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
12643  MemIndexPop(); \
12644  S128Push(); \
12645  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12646  }
12647  LOAD_SPLAT_CASE(Load8Splat)
12648  LOAD_SPLAT_CASE(Load16Splat)
12649  LOAD_SPLAT_CASE(Load32Splat)
12650  LOAD_SPLAT_CASE(Load64Splat)
12651 #undef LOAD_SPLAT_CASE
12652 
12653 #define LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(op) \
12654  case kExprS128##op: { \
12655  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC( \
12656  s2s_SimdS128##op, s2s_SimdS128##op##_Idx64, is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
12657  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
12658  MemIndexPop(); \
12659  S128Push(); \
12660  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12661  }
12662  LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(Load8x8S)
12663  LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(Load8x8U)
12664  LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(Load16x4S)
12665  LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(Load16x4U)
12666  LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(Load32x2S)
12667  LOAD_EXTEND_CASE(Load32x2U)
12668 #undef LOAD_EXTEND_CASE
12669 
12670 #define LOAD_ZERO_EXTEND_CASE(op, load_type) \
12671  case kExprS128##op: { \
12672  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC( \
12673  s2s_SimdS128##op, s2s_SimdS128##op##_Idx64, is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
12674  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
12675  MemIndexPop(); \
12676  S128Push(); \
12677  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12678  }
12679  LOAD_ZERO_EXTEND_CASE(Load32Zero, I32)
12680  LOAD_ZERO_EXTEND_CASE(Load64Zero, I64)
12681 #undef LOAD_ZERO_EXTEND_CASE
12682 
12683 #define LOAD_LANE_CASE(op) \
12684  case kExprS128##op: { \
12685  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC( \
12686  s2s_SimdS128##op, s2s_SimdS128##op##_Idx64, is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
12687  S128Pop(); \
12688  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.simd_loadstore_lane.offset); \
12689  MemIndexPop(); \
12690  /* emit 8 bits ? */ \
12691  EmitI16Const(instr.optional.simd_loadstore_lane.lane); \
12692  S128Push(); \
12693  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12694  }
12695  LOAD_LANE_CASE(Load8Lane)
12696  LOAD_LANE_CASE(Load16Lane)
12697  LOAD_LANE_CASE(Load32Lane)
12698  LOAD_LANE_CASE(Load64Lane)
12699 #undef LOAD_LANE_CASE
12700 
12701 #define STORE_LANE_CASE(op) \
12702  case kExprS128##op: { \
12703  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC( \
12704  s2s_SimdS128##op, s2s_SimdS128##op##_Idx64, is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
12705  S128Pop(); \
12706  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.simd_loadstore_lane.offset); \
12707  MemIndexPop(); \
12708  /* emit 8 bits ? */ \
12709  EmitI16Const(instr.optional.simd_loadstore_lane.lane); \
12710  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12711  }
12712  STORE_LANE_CASE(Store8Lane)
12713  STORE_LANE_CASE(Store16Lane)
12714  STORE_LANE_CASE(Store32Lane)
12715  STORE_LANE_CASE(Store64Lane)
12716 #undef STORE_LANE_CASE
12717 
12718 #define EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE_CASE(op) \
12719  case kExpr##op: { \
12720  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Simd##op); \
12721  S128Pop(); \
12722  S128Push(); \
12723  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
12724  }
12725  EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE_CASE(I32x4ExtAddPairwiseI16x8S)
12726  EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE_CASE(I32x4ExtAddPairwiseI16x8U)
12727  EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE_CASE(I16x8ExtAddPairwiseI8x16S)
12728  EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE_CASE(I16x8ExtAddPairwiseI8x16U)
12729 #undef EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE_CASE
12730 
12731  default:
12732  FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s",
12733  wasm_code_->start[instr.pc],
12734  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(
12735  static_cast<WasmOpcode>(wasm_code_->start[instr.pc])));
12736  UNREACHABLE();
12737  }
12738 
12739  return RegMode::kNoReg;
12740 }
12741 
12742 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::EncodeSuperInstruction(
12743  RegMode& reg_mode, const WasmInstruction& curr_instr,
12744  const WasmInstruction& next_instr) {
12745  if (!v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
12746  DCHECK_EQ(handler_size_, InstrHandlerSize::Large);
12747  return DoEncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr);
12748  }
12749 
12750  size_t current_instr_code_offset = code_.size();
12751  size_t current_slots_size = slots_.size();
12752  current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
12753  handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Small;
12754  stack_.clear_history();
12755 
12756  bool result = DoEncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr);
12757  if (result && current_instr_encoding_failed_) {
12758  code_.resize(current_instr_code_offset);
12759  slots_.resize(current_slots_size);
12760  stack_.rollback();
12761  current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
12762  handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Large;
12763  result = DoEncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr);
12764  DCHECK(!current_instr_encoding_failed_);
12765  }
12766 
12767  return result;
12768 }
12769 
12770 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::DoEncodeSuperInstruction(
12771  RegMode& reg_mode, const WasmInstruction& curr_instr,
12772  const WasmInstruction& next_instr) {
12773  if (curr_instr.orig >= kExprI32LoadMem &&
12774  curr_instr.orig <= kExprI64LoadMem32U &&
12775  next_instr.orig == kExprLocalSet) {
12776  // Do not optimize if we are updating a shared slot.
12777  uint32_t to_stack_index = next_instr.optional.index;
12778  if (HasSharedSlot(to_stack_index)) return false;
12779 
12780  switch (curr_instr.orig) {
12781 // The implementation of r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet is identical to the
12782 // implementation of r2s_LoadMem, so we can reuse the same builtin.
12783 #define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
12784  case kExpr##name: { \
12785  if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) { \
12786  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name##_LocalSet, \
12787  s2s_##name##_LocalSet_Idx64, \
12788  is_memory64_, curr_instr.pc); \
12789  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset); \
12790  MemIndexPop(); \
12791  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[to_stack_index]].slot_offset); \
12792  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg; \
12793  } else { \
12794  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_##name, r2s_##name##_Idx64, \
12795  is_memory64_, curr_instr.pc); \
12796  EmitMemoryOffset(static_cast<uint64_t>(curr_instr.optional.offset)); \
12797  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[to_stack_index]].slot_offset); \
12798  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg; \
12799  } \
12800  return true; \
12801  }
12802  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8S, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
12803  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);
12804  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16S, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
12805  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);
12806  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8S, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
12807  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
12808  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
12809  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
12810  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
12811  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);
12812  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
12813  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
12814  LOAD_CASE(F32LoadMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
12815  LOAD_CASE(F64LoadMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
12816 #undef LOAD_CASE
12817 
12818  default:
12819  return false;
12820  }
12821  } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprI32LoadMem &&
12822  next_instr.orig == kExprI32StoreMem) {
12823  if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12824  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32LoadStoreMem,
12825  s2s_I32LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12826  curr_instr.pc);
12827  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset); // load_offset
12828  MemIndexPop(); // load_index
12829  } else {
12830  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_I32LoadStoreMem,
12831  r2s_I32LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12832  curr_instr.pc);
12833  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset); // load_offset
12834  }
12835  EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset); // store_offset
12836  MemIndexPop(); // store_index
12837  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12838  return true;
12839  } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprI64LoadMem &&
12840  next_instr.orig == kExprI64StoreMem) {
12841  if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12842  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64LoadStoreMem,
12843  s2s_I64LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12844  curr_instr.pc);
12845  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12846  MemIndexPop();
12847  } else {
12848  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_I64LoadStoreMem,
12849  r2s_I64LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12850  curr_instr.pc);
12851  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12852  }
12853  EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset);
12854  MemIndexPop();
12855  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12856  return true;
12857  } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprF32LoadMem &&
12858  next_instr.orig == kExprF32StoreMem) {
12859  if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12860  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32LoadStoreMem,
12861  s2s_F32LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12862  curr_instr.pc);
12863  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12864  MemIndexPop();
12865  } else {
12866  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_F32LoadStoreMem,
12867  r2s_F32LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12868  curr_instr.pc);
12869  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12870  }
12871  EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset);
12872  MemIndexPop();
12873  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12874  return true;
12875  } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprF64LoadMem &&
12876  next_instr.orig == kExprF64StoreMem) {
12877  if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12878  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64LoadStoreMem,
12879  s2s_F64LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12880  curr_instr.pc);
12881  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12882  MemIndexPop();
12883  } else {
12884  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_F64LoadStoreMem,
12885  r2s_F64LoadStoreMem_Idx64, is_memory64_,
12886  curr_instr.pc);
12887  EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12888  }
12889  EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset);
12890  MemIndexPop();
12891  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12892  return true;
12893  } else if (curr_instr.orig >= kExprI32Const &&
12894  curr_instr.orig <= kExprF32Const &&
12895  next_instr.orig == kExprLocalSet) {
12896  uint32_t to_stack_index = next_instr.optional.index;
12897  switch (curr_instr.orig) {
12898  case kExprI32Const: {
12899  uint32_t from_slot_index =
12900  CreateConstSlot<int32_t>(curr_instr.optional.i32);
12901  CopyToSlot(kWasmI32, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12902  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12903  return true;
12904  }
12905  case kExprI64Const: {
12906  uint32_t from_slot_index =
12907  CreateConstSlot<int64_t>(curr_instr.optional.i64);
12908  CopyToSlot(kWasmI64, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12909  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12910  return true;
12911  }
12912  case kExprF32Const: {
12913  uint32_t from_slot_index =
12914  CreateConstSlot<float>(curr_instr.optional.f32);
12915  CopyToSlot(kWasmF32, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12916  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12917  return true;
12918  }
12919  case kExprF64Const: {
12920  uint32_t from_slot_index =
12921  CreateConstSlot<double>(curr_instr.optional.f64);
12922  CopyToSlot(kWasmF64, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12923  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12924  return true;
12925  }
12926  default:
12927  return false;
12928  }
12929  } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprLocalGet &&
12930  next_instr.orig >= kExprI32StoreMem &&
12931  next_instr.orig <= kExprI64StoreMem32) {
12932  switch (next_instr.orig) {
12933 // The implementation of r2s_LocalGet_StoreMem is identical to the
12934 // implementation of r2s_StoreMem, so we can reuse the same builtin.
12935 #define STORE_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
12936  case kExpr##name: { \
12937  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, s2s_##name##_Idx64, \
12938  is_memory64_, curr_instr.pc); \
12939  EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[curr_instr.optional.index]].slot_offset); \
12940  EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset); \
12941  MemIndexPop(); \
12942  reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg; \
12943  return true; \
12944  }
12945  STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem8, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
12946  STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem16, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
12947  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem8, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
12948  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem16, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
12949  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem32, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
12950  STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
12951  STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
12952  STORE_CASE(F32StoreMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
12953  STORE_CASE(F64StoreMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
12954 #undef STORE_CASE
12955 
12956  default:
12957  return false;
12958  }
12959  }
12960 
12961  return false;
12962 }
12963 
12964 std::unique_ptr<WasmBytecode> WasmBytecodeGenerator::GenerateBytecode() {
12965 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
12966  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_bytecode_generator) {
12967  printf("\nGenerate bytecode for function: %d\n", function_index_);
12968  }
12969 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
12970 
12971  uint32_t const_slots = ScanConstInstructions();
12972  const_slots_values_.resize(const_slots * kSlotSize);
12973 
12974  pc_t pc = wasm_code_->locals.encoded_size;
12975  RegMode reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12976 
12977  Decoder decoder(wasm_code_->start, wasm_code_->end);
12978 
12979  current_block_index_ = -1;
12980 
12981  // Init stack_ with return values, args and local types.
12982 
12983  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < return_count_; index++) {
12984  CreateSlot(wasm_code_->function->sig->GetReturn(index));
12985  }
12986 
12987  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < args_count_; index++) {
12988  _PushSlot(wasm_code_->function->sig->GetParam(index));
12989  }
12990 
12991  // Reserve space for const slots
12992  slot_offset_ += const_slots;
12993 
12994  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < wasm_code_->locals.num_locals; index++) {
12995  _PushSlot(wasm_code_->locals.local_types[index]);
12996  }
12997 
12998  current_block_index_ = BeginBlock(
12999  kExprBlock,
13000  {wasm_code_->function->sig_index, kWasmBottom.raw_bit_field()});
13001 
13002  WasmInstruction curr_instr;
13003  WasmInstruction next_instr;
13004 
13005  pc_t limit = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
13006  while (pc < limit) {
13007  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(wasm_code_->start);
13008 
13009  if (!curr_instr) {
13010  curr_instr = DecodeInstruction(pc, decoder);
13011  if (curr_instr) pc += curr_instr.length;
13012  }
13013  if (!curr_instr) break;
13014  DCHECK(!next_instr);
13015  next_instr = DecodeInstruction(pc, decoder);
13016  if (next_instr) pc += next_instr.length;
13017 
13018  if (next_instr) {
13019  if (v8_flags.drumbrake_super_instructions && is_instruction_reachable_ &&
13020  EncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr)) {
13021  curr_instr = {};
13022  next_instr = {};
13023  } else {
13024  reg_mode =
13025  EncodeInstruction(curr_instr, reg_mode, next_instr.InputRegMode());
13026  curr_instr = next_instr;
13027  next_instr = {};
13028  }
13029  } else {
13030  reg_mode = EncodeInstruction(curr_instr, reg_mode, RegMode::kNoReg);
13031  curr_instr = {};
13032  }
13033 
13034  if (pc == limit && curr_instr) {
13035  reg_mode = EncodeInstruction(curr_instr, reg_mode, RegMode::kNoReg);
13036  }
13037  }
13038 
13039  PatchLoopBeginInstructions();
13040  PatchBranchOffsets();
13041 
13042  total_bytecode_size_ += code_.size();
13043 
13044  CanonicalTypeIndex canonical_sig_index =
13045  module_->canonical_sig_id(module_->functions[function_index_].sig_index);
13046  const CanonicalSig* canonicalized_sig =
13047  GetTypeCanonicalizer()->LookupFunctionSignature(canonical_sig_index);
13048  return std::make_unique<WasmBytecode>(
13049  function_index_, code_.data(), code_.size(), slot_offset_,
13050  module_->functions[function_index_].sig, canonicalized_sig, wasm_code_,
13051  blocks_.size(), const_slots_values_.data(), const_slots_values_.size(),
13052  ref_slots_count_, std::move(eh_data_), std::move(code_pc_map_));
13053 }
13054 
13055 int32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::BeginBlock(
13056  WasmOpcode opcode, const WasmInstruction::Optional::Block signature) {
13057  int32_t block_index = static_cast<int32_t>(blocks_.size());
13058  uint32_t stack_size = this->stack_size();
13059 
13060  uint32_t first_block_index = 0;
13061  size_t rets_slots_count = 0;
13062  size_t params_slots_count = 0;
13063  if (block_index > 0 && (opcode != kExprElse && opcode != kExprCatch &&
13064  opcode != kExprCatchAll)) {
13065  first_block_index = ReserveBlockSlots(opcode, signature, &rets_slots_count,
13066  &params_slots_count);
13067  }
13068 
13069  uint32_t parent_block_index = current_block_index_;
13070  if (opcode == kExprCatch || opcode == kExprCatchAll) {
13071  parent_block_index =
13072  blocks_[eh_data_.GetCurrentTryBlockIndex()].parent_block_index_;
13073  }
13074 
13075  blocks_.emplace_back(opcode, CurrentCodePos(), parent_block_index, stack_size,
13076  signature, first_block_index, rets_slots_count,
13077  params_slots_count, eh_data_.GetCurrentTryBlockIndex());
13078  current_block_index_ = block_index;
13079 
13080  if (opcode == kExprIf && params_slots_count > 0) {
13081  DCHECK_GE(stack_size, params_slots_count);
13082  blocks_.back().SaveParams(&stack_[stack_size - params_slots_count],
13083  params_slots_count);
13084  }
13085 
13086  if (opcode == kExprLoop) {
13087  StoreBlockParamsIntoSlots(current_block_index_, true);
13088  loop_begin_code_offsets_.push_back(CurrentCodePos());
13089  blocks_[current_block_index_].begin_code_offset_ = CurrentCodePos();
13090  last_instr_offset_ = kInvalidCodeOffset;
13091 
13092  START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(s2s_OnLoopBegin) {}
13093  END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
13094  }
13095  return current_block_index_;
13096 }
13097 
13098 int WasmBytecodeGenerator::GetCurrentTryBlockIndex(
13099  bool return_matching_try_for_catch_blocks) const {
13100  DCHECK_GE(current_block_index_, 0);
13101  int index = current_block_index_;
13102  while (index >= 0) {
13103  const auto& block = blocks_[index];
13104  if (block.IsTry()) return index;
13105  if (return_matching_try_for_catch_blocks &&
13106  (block.IsCatch() || block.IsCatchAll())) {
13107  return block.parent_try_block_index_;
13108  }
13109  index = blocks_[index].parent_block_index_;
13110  }
13111  return -1;
13112 }
13113 
13114 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PatchLoopBeginInstructions() {
13115  if (ref_slots_count_ == 0) {
13116  for (size_t i = 0; i < loop_begin_code_offsets_.size(); i++) {
13117  base::WriteUnalignedValue<InstructionHandler>(
13118  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + loop_begin_code_offsets_[i]),
13119  k_s2s_OnLoopBeginNoRefSlots);
13120  }
13121  }
13122 }
13123 
13124 void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PatchBranchOffsets() {
13125  static const uint32_t kElseBlockStartOffset =
13126  sizeof(InstructionHandler) + sizeof(uint32_t);
13127 
13128  for (int block_index = 0; block_index < static_cast<int>(blocks_.size());
13129  block_index++) {
13130  const BlockData block_data = blocks_[block_index];
13131  for (size_t i = 0; i < block_data.branch_code_offsets_.size(); i++) {
13132  uint32_t current_code_offset = block_data.branch_code_offsets_[i];
13133  uint32_t target_offset = block_data.end_code_offset_;
13134  if (block_data.IsLoop()) {
13135  target_offset = block_data.begin_code_offset_;
13136  } else if (block_data.IsIf() && block_data.if_else_block_index_ >= 0 &&
13137  current_code_offset == block_data.begin_code_offset_) {
13138  // Jumps to the 'else' branch.
13139  target_offset =
13140  blocks_[block_data.if_else_block_index_].begin_code_offset_ +
13141  kElseBlockStartOffset;
13142  } else if ((block_data.IsCatch() || block_data.IsCatchAll()) &&
13143  current_code_offset == block_data.begin_code_offset_ +
13144  sizeof(InstructionHandler)) {
13145  // Jumps to the end of a sequence of 'try'/'catch' branches.
13146  target_offset = static_cast<uint32_t>(
13147  eh_data_.GetEndInstructionOffsetFor(block_index));
13148  }
13149 
13150  int32_t delta = target_offset - current_code_offset;
13151  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
13152  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + current_code_offset), delta);
13153  }
13154  }
13155 }
13156 
13157 bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::TryCompactInstructionHandler(
13158  InstructionHandler func_id) {
13159  if (last_instr_offset_ == kInvalidCodeOffset) return false;
13160  InstructionHandler* prev_instr_addr =
13161  reinterpret_cast<InstructionHandler*>(code_.data() + last_instr_offset_);
13162  InstructionHandler prev_instr_handler = *prev_instr_addr;
13163  if (func_id == k_s2s_CopySlot32 && prev_instr_handler == k_s2s_CopySlot32) {
13164  // Tranforms:
13165  // [CopySlot32: InstrId][from: slot_offset_t][to: slot_offset_t]
13166  // into:
13167  // [CopySlot32x2: InstrId][from0: slot_offset_t][to0: slot_offset_t][from1:
13168  // slot_offset_t][to1: slot_offset_t]
13169  DCHECK(handler_size_ == InstrHandlerSize::Large ||
13170  v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode);
13171  base::WriteUnalignedValue<InstructionHandler>(
13172  reinterpret_cast<Address>(prev_instr_addr), k_s2s_CopySlot32x2);
13173  return true;
13174  } else if (func_id == k_s2s_CopySlot64 &&
13175  prev_instr_handler == k_s2s_CopySlot64) {
13176  DCHECK(handler_size_ == InstrHandlerSize::Large ||
13177  v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode);
13178  base::WriteUnalignedValue<InstructionHandler>(
13179  reinterpret_cast<Address>(prev_instr_addr), k_s2s_CopySlot64x2);
13180  return true;
13181  }
13182  return false;
13183 }
13184 
13185 ClearThreadInWasmScope::ClearThreadInWasmScope(Isolate* isolate)
13186  : isolate_(isolate) {
13187  DCHECK_IMPLIES(trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled(),
13188  trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm());
13189  trap_handler::ClearThreadInWasm();
13190 }
13191 
13192 ClearThreadInWasmScope ::~ClearThreadInWasmScope() {
13193  DCHECK_IMPLIES(trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled(),
13194  !trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm());
13195  if (!isolate_->has_exception()) {
13196  trap_handler::SetThreadInWasm();
13197  }
13198  // Otherwise we only want to set the flag if the exception is caught in
13199  // wasm. This is handled by the unwinder.
13200 }
